            <main class="panel">
                <section id="billing" class="section case-page" style="display:none;">

                    <h2>Billing</h2>
                    <div class="hr case-page"></div>
                    <p>
                        The Billing Section allows you to manage all financial aspects of your matters in one place.
                        It consolidates Invoice Management, Expense Management, and Time Entry Management,
                        ensuring accurate billing, transparency, and effective cost tracking.
                    </p>

                    <h4>Invoice Management</h4>

                    <p>
                        In the Invoice Management section, you can view all invoices saved in the tool,
                        including details such as invoice name, matter name, invoice status, amount,
                        and other customizable fields.
                    </p>

                    <div class="case-page">
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/INV1.png" alt="addcase Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <p>
                        At the top of the screen, you can view the Total Amount, Total Collected Amount,
                        and Total Overdue Amount.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        You can also use filters to refine your search by Client Name, Created Date,
                        Amount, and other parameters.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        From <strong>Customize</strong> option, you can add more columns to your list temporarily.
                    </p>

                    <p>To create a new invoice, please follow the below steps:</p>

                    <div class="case-page">
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/INV2.png" alt="addcase Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <ul>
                        <li>Click on <strong>Create Invoice</strong> button   <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/CREATE_INVOICE.png" />  and a new form will open.</li>
                        <li>
                            Now, you can choose the client details for whom you want to raise the invoice
                            like Client Name, Client Address, Mobile Number, PAN and GST, etc.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Further you can add the Biller Details, Invoice Details such as Invoice Name,
                            Invoice Date, Due Date, Particulars and Amount, etc.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Once all the details are added, please click on <strong>Save Invoice</strong>
                            button to create the new invoice.
                        </li>
                    </ul>



                    <p>
                        Under the Invoice list, you will have some action buttons against each invoice.
                        Please find below the explanation of each action button:
                    </p>

                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Pay amount</strong><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/AMOUNT.png" /> – can be used to mark the payment status of the invoice and log the amount details.</li>
                        <li><strong>Share Invoice</strong><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/SHARE.png" /> – can be used to share the invoice to the client directly from the system, provided the client has access to Mykase with the client credentials.</li>
                        <li><strong>Amend Invoice</strong><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/AMEND.png" /> – can be used to amend the invoice.</li>
                        <li><strong>Cancel Invoice</strong><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/CANCEL.png" /> – can be used to cancel the invoice.</li>
                        <li><strong>Recurring Invoice</strong><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/RECURRING.png" /> – can be used to create a recurring invoice.</li>
                        <li><strong>Share as mail</strong><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/email.png" /> – can be used to mail the invoice to someone on an email with the remarks.</li>
                        <li><strong>Version History</strong><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/VERSION.png" /> – can be used to download the original invoice or amended invoice into your system.</li>
                    </ul>



                    <p>
                        To configure or edit the invoice settings such as invoice template, company details,
                        logo, signature, invoice series, tax addition, etc., please follow the below steps:
                    </p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Click on the <strong>Invoice Setting</strong> button <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/AMOUNT.png" /> and click on
                            <strong>Invoice Setting</strong> option from the dropdown.
                        </li>

                        <div class="case-page">
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/INV3.png" alt="addcase Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                        </div>


                        <li>
                            On the invoice setting page, select the invoice template, upload the company logo,
                            upload the signature that should be incorporated with every invoice.
                        </li>
                        <li>Add the company details, invoice noted and terms &amp; conditions.</li>
                        <li>
                            You can also add the tax rates by following the below steps:
                            <ul>
                                <li>Click on Tax button under the invoice settings. </li>

                                <div class="case-page">
                                    <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/INV4.png" alt="addcase Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                                </div>

                                <li>Under the Create Tax Rates tab, select the tax type as SGST, CGST and IGST. </li>
                                <li>Enter the tax percentage and click on Save button.  </li>

                                <div class="case-page">
                                    <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/INV5.png" alt="addcase Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                                </div>

                                <li>
                                    The added tax rates can be viewed under the View Tax Rates tab, from where you can delete the tax rates or download a compiled excel.
                                </li>

                                <li>
                                    To build an invoice series, you can click on Invoice Series button and follow the below steps:
                                    <div class="case-page">
                                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/INV6.png" alt="addcase Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                                    </div>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>
                                            Under the Create Invoice Series tab, you can select the parameters you want
                                            in your invoice series by checking the box.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            Further, you can select the type of Prefix/Suffix, Month type, FY/CY
                                            and the operator of your own choice from the dropdown.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            Decide the sequence of the parameters and click on <strong>Check Preview</strong>
                                            option to see how the invoice series will look.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            Once all the changes are done, click on <strong>Save</strong> to update the series.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            The created invoice series can be viewed under <strong>View Invoice Series</strong> tab,
                                            from where it can be deleted or exported.
                                        </li>
                                    </ul>

                                </li>

                                <li>
                                    You can add multiple biller address which can be selected while creating the invoice, by following the below steps:
                                    <div class="case-page">
                                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/INV7.png" alt="addcase Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                                    </div>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>
                                            Click on the <strong>Biller Address List</strong> option  under the invoice settings page.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            Click on the <strong>Add Address</strong> button and add the required details such as
                                            Company, Address, State, Phone number, etc.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            You can also set this biller address as default by toggling the
                                            <strong>Set as Default</strong> button.
                                        </li>
                                    </ul>

                                </li>

                                <li>
                                    For any payment made by cheque, you can mark the payment as Clear or Bounced by following the below steps:

                                    <ul>


                                        <li>
                                            Click on the Invoice Setting button and choose Clear Payment option from the dropdown on the Invoice page.
                                        </li>
                                        <div class="case-page">
                                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/INV8.png" alt="addcase Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                                        </div>


                                        <li>
                                            On the screen, you have to select the client first, for which you have created
                                            the invoice and logged the cheque payment.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            Then, you need to select the invoice for which the cheque is added.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            All the cheque payments will appear in the list below from where you can
                                            mark the payment as <strong>Clear</strong> or <strong>Bounce</strong>.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            Once you click on any of the two options, you can add the date of clearance
                                            or bounce respectively and click on <strong>Save</strong> to update it.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            If the cheque payment is marked as clear, it will be added into the
                                            <strong>Payment Made</strong> section for that invoice.
                                        </li>
                                    </ul>

                                </li>
                            </ul>



                        </li>


                        @*<div class="case-page">
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/INV4.png" alt="addcase Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>


                            <li>
                                Under the Create Tax Rates tab, select the tax type as SGST, CGST and IGST.
                            </li>
                            <li>Enter the tax percentage and click on <strong>Save</strong> button.</li>*@











                    </ul>



                </section>

                <section id="expense" class="section case-page">
                    <!-- ================= Expense Management ================= -->

                    <h2>Expense Management</h2>
                    <div class="hr case-page"></div>
                    <p>
                        The Expense Management Section in <b>Mykase</b> is designed to help legal teams and
                        professionals maintain a clear and accurate record of all expenses related to
                        matters, clients, or projects.
                    </p>
                    <div class="case-page">
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/EXP_MAN1.png" alt="addcase Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>



                    <p>
                        At the top of the screen, you can view the <b>Total Amount</b>, <b>Total Amount Made</b>,
                        and <b>Total Pending Amount</b>.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        You can also use filters to refine your search by <b>Category</b>, <b>Retainer Name</b>,
                        <b>Expense Status</b>, and other parameters.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        From the <b>Customize</b> option, you can add more columns to your list temporarily.
                    </p>

                    <h3>To create a new expense, please follow the below steps:</h3>

                    <div class="case-page">
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/EXP_MAN2.png" alt="addcase Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Click on the <b>Create Expense</b> button and a new form will open.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Now, you can enter the client and matter details for which you are creating the expense.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Further, you can add the expense details such as <b>Expense Date</b>, <b>Category</b>,
                            <b>Amount</b>, <b>Due Date</b>, etc.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            You can also attach a receipt or invoice for the expense through the
                            <b>Upload Document</b> option in the form.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Once all the details are added, click on <b>Add Item</b> button to save the expense.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <h4>Under the Expense list, you will have some action buttons against each expense. Please find below the explanation of each action button: </h4>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <b>Edit Expense</b> <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/VIEW_PEN.png" /> – can be used to edit the expense details such as
                            Retainer Name, Expense Type, Amount, etc.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <b>Pay Expense</b><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/AMOUNT.png" /> – can be used to log the amount that has been paid under the expense.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <b>Delete Expense</b><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/tdel.png" /> – can be used to delete the expense.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <p>To change the status of any expense, please follow the below steps:</p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Select the expenses by clicking the checkbox in the first column for the entries
                            whose status you want to update.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Click on the <b>Change Status</b> button on the top-right corner under the Expense module.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Once confirmed, the expense status will toggle between <b>Paid</b> and <b>Unpaid</b>.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <p>
                        You can also download the entire list of all expenses by clicking on the
                        <b>Download</b> button <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/down.png" /> and choosing the option of <b>Excel</b> or <b>PDF</b>
                        as per your requirement.
                    </p>

                    <!-- ================= End Expense Management ================= -->

                </section>



                <section id="time-entry" class="section case-page">

                    <h2>Time Entry Management</h2>
                    <div class="hr case-page"></div>
                    <p>
                        The Time Entry Section is a key part of Mykase that allows legal teams to meticulously
                        track the time spent on every task or activity associated with a matter. Time tracking is
                        critical for productivity analysis and internal auditing. By maintaining detailed time
                        records, firms can ensure that every minute spent on a case is accounted for, improving
                        transparency and profitability.
                    </p>

                    <div class="case-page">
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/TIMEENTRY1.png" alt="addcase Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <p>
                        At the top of the screen, you can view the Total Hours Logged, Total Billable Hours,
                        and Total Non-Billable Hours.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        You can also use filters to refine your search by Task Date, Entry Type, Matter Name
                        and other parameters.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        From <strong>Customize</strong> option, you can add more columns to your list temporarily.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        You can also download the entire list of all time entries by clicking on the
                        <strong>Download</strong> button and choose the option of Excel or PDF as per your
                        requirement.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        In case any time entry is marked as WIP instead of Billable or Non-Billable, you can
                        click on the <strong>Convert Time Entry Type</strong> button <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/QUESTION.png" /> to change it.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        To change the status of any time entry, please follow the below steps:
                    </p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Select the time entries by clicking the checkbox in the first column for the entries
                            whose status you want to update.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Now click on the <strong>Change Status</strong> button the top-right corner under the
                            Time Entry module.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Once confirmed, the time entry status will change to Billed, indicating that it has
                            been included in an invoice. This action cannot be reversed.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <p>
                        To log a new Time Entry, please follow the below steps:
                    </p>

                    <div class="case-page">
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/TIMEENTRY2.png" alt="addcase Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Under the Time Entry Module, click on the <strong>Create Time Entry</strong> button <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/CREATE_TIME_ENTRY.png" />
                            and a new popup will open.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Now, you can add the details in the popup such as Type and Matter Name.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Add the Task Type for which you are logging the time entry. You can also add a
                            new task type if it is already not there in the list.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Then add the date of the task in the next column and you can also add a note
                            along with an attachment.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            To log the time entry, you can either manually add the hr/min/sec or start the
                            timer by pressing the play button <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/PLAY.png" /> and once you have completed the task, you
                            can click on pause button <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/PAUSE.png" /> to stop the timer.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                </section>

            </main>
        </div>
