                <section class="section case-page" id="dash" style="display:none;">
                    <h2>Dashboard</h2>
                    <div class="hr case-page"></div>
                    <p>
                        The <strong>Dashboard</strong> provides a comprehensive overview of the litigation management tool, offering a snapshot of your case portfolio.
                        It displays a summary of key metrics, including the total number of <strong>matters</strong>, <strong>clients</strong>, <strong>tasks due today </strong> and <strong>archived matters</strong>.
                    </p><p>
                        Additionally, you will find customizable widgets that offer insights based on the matters you have entered into the tool. You can select and display any 4 widgets from a choice of 9 available
                        options to tailor the dashboard to your needs.
                    </p>

                    @*<p>
                            Additionally, the Dashboard allows quick access to your <strong>To-Do List</strong>, <strong>Notes</strong>, and <strong>Contacts</strong>.
                            You can also track your <strong>Login Activity</strong> by applying filters based on a specific date range.
                        </p>*@

                    @*<p>
                            You can click on the <strong>Mykase Logo</strong> or go to <strong>Matter → Dashboard</strong> from any module.
                        </p>*@


                    <div class="text-center mt-3 case-page">
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/DashBoard.png" alt="Dashboard Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>
                    @*<p>
                            To learn how to use the <strong>Case Tracking</strong> module, click the <strong>"How Case Tracking Works"</strong> option located next to <strong>My Dashboard</strong>.
                            This will provide you with <strong>step-by-step instructional videos</strong> for easy understanding.
                        </p>*@
                </section>

                <section class="section case-page" id="account-details" style="display:none;">
                    <h2>Account Details </h2>
                    <div class="hr case-page"></div>
                    <p>
                        The Account Details section in Mykase provides a complete overview of your organization’s subscription plan and usage status. It helps you keep track of your active plan, renewal dates, and available quota — ensuring uninterrupted access to all features and modules.
                    </p>
                    <p>To access the account details, you can follow the below steps: </p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Click your <strong>Profile Placeholder</strong> icon
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/profileplace.png"
                                 alt="Profile placeholder icon" />
                            located at the top-right corner.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            Select <strong>Account Details</strong> from the dropdown menu.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            The screen will display your plan details, subscription dates, and quota information.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section class="section case-page" id="admin-controls">
                    <!-- ================= ADMIN CONTROLS ================= -->

                    <h2>Admin Controls</h2>
                    <div class="hr case-page"></div>
                    <p>
                        The <strong>Admin Controls</strong> section in <strong>Mykase</strong> allows
                        administrator to manage users, define organizational configurations,
                        transfer work, and assign rights across the platform. This section provides
                        complete administrative access to ensure smooth functioning, user
                        accountability, and secure data management within the organization’s
                        Mykase account.
                    </p>

                    <!-- ================= MANAGE USERS ================= -->

                    <h4>Manage Users</h4>

                    <p>
                        The <strong>Manage Users</strong> section allows the admin to add a new user
                        or edit and manage all users within the organization’s Mykase account.
                    </p>

                    <h4>Key Features</h4>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Add New User:</strong><br />
                            Create a new user profile by entering basic details such as name, email
                            address, department, designation, and role.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <p>To do the same, please follow the below steps:</p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Click on the <strong>Profile Placeholder Icon</strong> on the top right corner
                            and select <strong>Manage Users</strong> from the dropdown menu.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            The user list will open where you can see all the previously added users.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Click on the <strong>Add New User</strong> button<img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/ADD_NEW_USER.png" /> , post which the user
                            addition form will open.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <div class="case-page">
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/ADMIN_CONTROLS1.png" alt="addcase Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>
                    <p>
                        First, you need to select the type of user:
                    </p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <strong>User:</strong>
                            A user with limited access rights, defined and controlled by the Admin or
                            Partner. Users typically have restricted visibility and functionality
                            depending on assigned rights.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Partner:</strong>
                            A partner generally has higher privileges, somewhat similar to the Admin,
                            but their rights and permissions are still controlled and managed by the Admin.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <p>
                        If you are selecting the user type as <strong>User</strong>, then you can also
                        map the user under a partner as a hierarchy.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        Now, you can enter further basic information such as Name, Mobile Number,
                        Email and Employee code.
                    </p>

                    <p>If required, you can add:</p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Contact information</strong> like landline, extension and address.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Professional information</strong> like designation, branch,
                            department and reporting manager.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Employment details</strong> like Qualification, PQE, Experience with firm,
                            Areas of Expertise, Bar Registration Number, Hourly Rate (Rs/Hour) and
                            Additional Information.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <p>
                        Once all the details are added, please click on the
                        <strong>Save User Details</strong> button <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/SAVE_USER_DETAIL.png" /> to create the user.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        After the user creation, you also need to create their credentials
                        (User ID and Password), through which they can login into their account.
                    </p>

                    <div class="case-page">
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/ADMIN_CONTROLS2.png" alt="addcase Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>


                    <!-- ================= CREATE CREDENTIALS ================= -->



                    <p>Please follow the below steps to create the credentials:</p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            In the user list, click on the <strong>Add Credentials</strong> button for
                            the particular user.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            In the popup, enter a new User Id, Password and click on
                            <strong>Create</strong> to save the credentials.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Please note that we recommend creating a generic User ID instead of a
                            name-specific one, to avoid any hassle during the transition of the user
                            account holder.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Once the credentials are created, you can enable the user account by
                            toggling the <strong>Disabled</strong> button.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <!-- ================= EDIT USER DETAILS ================= -->

                    <h4>Edit or Update User Details</h4>

                    <p>
                        The <strong>Edit or Update User Details</strong> option allows the Admin or
                        Partner (with rights) to modify existing user information whenever required.
                        This feature ensures that all user data is up to date as organizational roles
                        or responsibilities change.
                    </p>

                    <p><strong>Steps to Edit User Details:</strong></p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>Go to <strong>Manage Users</strong>.</li>
                        <li>Search for the user using the search bar.</li>
                        <li>Click on the <strong>Edit</strong> icon beside the user’s name.</li>
                        <li>
                            Make the required changes in name, email, mobile number, designation, etc.
                        </li>
                        <li>Click <strong>Save</strong> to confirm the updates.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <!-- ================= ENABLE / DISABLE USERS ================= -->

                    <h4>Enable / Disable Users</h4>

                    <p>
                        The <strong>Enable / Disable Users</strong> feature allows the admin to control
                        user access within the system. This ensures that only authorized and active
                        members can log in and perform actions, maintaining both security and data
                        integrity across the platform.  To enable or disable any user account, toggle the button under the
                        <strong>Status</strong> column in the User List.
                    </p>



                    <!-- ================= RESET PASSWORD ================= -->

                    <h4>Reset Password</h4>

                    <p>
                        The <strong>Reset Password</strong> option allows the Admin to help users regain
                        access to their accounts in case they forget their password or face login issues.
                    </p>

                    <p><strong>Steps to Reset Password:</strong></p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>Go to <strong>Manage Users</strong>.</li>
                        <li>Locate the user whose password needs to be reset.</li>
                        <li>
                            Click on the <strong>Reset Password</strong> button next to the user’s name.
                        </li>
                        <li>Enter the new password in the popup that opens.</li>
                        <li>Click on <strong>Submit</strong> to save the changes.</li>
                        <li>Share the new password securely with the user.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <!-- ================= VIEW ALL USERS ================= -->

                    <h4>View All Users</h4>

                    <p>
                        The <strong>Manage Users</strong> section provides the Admin/Partner with a
                        complete list of all users added to the organization’s Mykase account. This
                        includes both Users and Partners, along with their key details and current status.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        The search option helps Admins quickly locate specific users within the
                        organization’s user list. You can search for the user through a header based
                        on Username and Login User ID.
                    </p>

                    <h4>Organization Settings</h4>

                    <p>
                        The <strong>Organization Settings</strong> section provides a centralized place for Admins to configure
                        structural and operational details, ensuring smooth functioning, timely alerts, and consistent branding
                        across all users and modules of Mykase.
                    </p>

                    <p>Key Functions</p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Upload Logo</strong> –
                            You can add or update the organization’s logo, which will appear on dashboard and client portals
                            to ensure consistent branding.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <p>Please follow the below steps to upload the logo:</p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>Click on the <strong>Profile Placeholder</strong> icon and select <strong>Organization Settings</strong>.</li>
                        <li>Click on <strong>Upload Logo</strong> button <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/UPLOAD.png" /> on the top left corner.</li>
                        <li>Select any <strong>svg, jpg, png or gif</strong> file to upload as the logo.</li>
                        <li>
                            Please note that the image width should be less than or equal to <strong>160 px</strong> and height
                            less than or equal to <strong>40 px</strong>.
                        </li>
                    </ul>



                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Create Branch/Designation/Department</strong> –
                            The admin/partner can define and manage the organization’s structure by creating Branches,
                            Departments, and Designations, which can be mapped while creating the user accounts to ensure
                            the workspace mirrors the actual working structure of your organization.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <div class="case-page">
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/ADMIN_CONTROLS3.png" alt="addcase Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <p>To create the branch/designation/department, please follow the below steps:</p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>Click on the <strong>Profile Placeholder</strong> icon and select <strong>Organization Settings</strong>.</li>
                        <li>Click on <strong>Add New Category</strong> button <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/ADD_NEW_CATEGORY.png" /> on the top right.</li>
                        <li>
                            In the popup that opens, firstly select the type of structure you want to create,
                            i.e., <strong>Branch</strong>, <strong>Department</strong> or <strong>Designation</strong>.
                        </li>
                        <li>Next, enter the name of the Branch, Department or Designation.</li>
                        <li>Click on <strong>Confirm</strong> after completing the entries to update the structure.</li>
                    </ul>



                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Set Alerts On/Off</strong> –
                            The Set Alerts On/Off feature in the Organization Settings allows the Admin to manage whether users across the organization receive system-generated alerts and reminders. This helps maintain control over communication frequency and ensures that only relevant alerts are sent as per organizational preferences.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <div class="case-page">
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/ADMIN_CONTROLS4.png" alt="addcase Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <p>To set the alert on/off, please follow the below steps:</p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>Click on the <strong>Profile Placeholder</strong> icon and select <strong>Organization Settings</strong>.</li>
                        <li>
                            Click on <strong>Set Alert</strong> button <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/SET_ALERT.png" /> on the top right corner and choose
                            <strong>Set Alert</strong> option from the dropdown.
                        </li>
                        <li>In the popup that opens, select the user for which you want to enable or disable the alerts.</li>
                        <li>Then set the alert status as <strong>On/Off</strong> in the next option.</li>
                        <li>Click <strong>Confirm</strong> to apply the changes.</li>
                    </ul>


                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Set Alerts Days</strong> –
                            The Set Alert Days feature in the Organization Settings allows the Admin to define how many days in advance users should receive alerts or reminders for upcoming hearings. This ensures timely follow-ups and helps avoid missed dates or delays.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <div class="case-page">
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/ADMIN_CONTROLS5.png" alt="addcase Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <p>To set the alert days, please follow the below steps:</p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>Click on the <strong>Profile Placeholder</strong> icon and select <strong>Organization Settings</strong>.</li>
                        <li>
                            Click on <strong>Set Alert</strong> button <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/SET_ALERT.png" /> on the top right corner and choose
                            <strong>Set Alert Days</strong> option from the dropdown.
                        </li>
                        <li>In the popup that opens, select the user for which you want to set the alert days.</li>
                        <li>Then set the <strong>Alert Before Days</strong> in the next option.</li>
                        <li>Click <strong>Confirm</strong> to apply the changes.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h4>Work Transfer</h4>

                    <p>
                        The <strong>Work Transfer</strong> feature allows the admin to seamlessly reassign
                        all matters from one user to another. This functionality is especially useful
                        when an employee leaves the organization, goes on extended leave, or when there’s
                        a change in role or team structure. It ensures continuity of work without any
                        data loss or disruption.
                    </p>

                    <div class="case-page">
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/ADMIN_CONTROLS6.png" alt="addcase Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <p><b>Steps to do the Work Transfer:</b></p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Click on the <strong>Profile Placeholder</strong> icon and select
                            <strong>Work Transfer</strong>.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Firstly, select the <strong>From User</strong> from whom you want to transfer
                            the matters.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Now, under the <strong>Matter</strong> dropdown, select the matters which need
                            to be transferred. You can also select all matters at once.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Select the <strong>To User</strong> to whom the matters need to be transferred.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Click on the <strong>Transfer Matter</strong> button <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/TRANSFER_MATTER.png" /> to confirm the changes.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <p>
                        On the same screen, you can also see all the earlier transferred matters in the
                        <strong>Transfer List</strong>.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        You can also search any matter based on the Matter name and filter based on
                        <strong>From User</strong> or <strong>To User</strong>.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        The list can also be exported into Excel by clicking on the
                        <strong>Export</strong> button.
                    </p>

                    <h4>Rights</h4>

                    <p>
                        The <strong>Rights</strong> section under <strong>Admin Controls</strong> allows
                        the Admin to manage and customize user access across the platform. It ensures
                        that every user has appropriate permissions based on their role and
                        responsibilities within the organization. This section includes two key
                        components — <strong>Assigned Rights</strong> and <strong>Matter Rights</strong>.
                    </p>

                    <h4>Assigned Rights</h4>

                    <p>
                        The <strong>Assigned Rights</strong> feature enables the Admin to grant or restrict
                        access to specific modules or functionalities in Mykase. This helps maintain data
                        security, prevent unauthorized actions, and ensure users have access only to
                        what’s relevant to their role.
                    </p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Feature-Wise Control:</strong><br>
                            Enable or disable access to specific features such as Matter Management,
                            Task Management, Billing, Communication, or Reports.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Role-Based Customization:</strong><br>
                            Assign different rights for Users and Partners based on their organizational
                            role or designation.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Granular Permissions:</strong><br>
                            Control actions like viewing, adding, editing, or deleting within each module.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <p>
                        You can allow a Partner to create and edit rights for other users, while
                        restricting a User to only view the assigned rights.
                    </p>

                    <h4>To assign or edit Assigned Rights, you can follow the below steps:</h4>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Click on the <strong>Profile Placeholder</strong> icon and select
                            <strong>Rights</strong>.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            You will land on the <strong>Assigned Rights</strong> tab by default.
                        </li>


                        <div class="case-page">
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/ADMIN_CONTROLS7.png" alt="addcase Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                        </div>


                        <li>
                            Click on the <strong>Create New Rights</strong> button on the top right corner.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Now, select the type of Rights you want to give to the user i.e.
                            <strong>User Level Rights</strong>, <strong>Partner Level Rights</strong> or
                            <strong>View and Edit Only Rights</strong>.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Select the user/users to whom you want to assign these rights.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Choose the rights you want to provide by checking the boxes.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Click on <strong>Save</strong> button to confirm the changes.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            To edit the saved rights, click on the <strong>Edit</strong> button <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/VIEW_PEN.png" under the
                                                                                                     action tab for any particular user.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            To delete the saved rights, click on the <strong>Delete</strong> button <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/tdel.png" under
                                                                                                         the action tab for any particular user.
                        </li>
                    </ul>



                    <h4>Matter Rights</h4>

                    <p>
                        The <strong>Matter Rights</strong> feature allows the Admin to set or modify
                        permissions at an individual matter level. It provides finer control over who
                        can view, edit, create, or export information related to specific matters.
                    </p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Matter-Wise Permission Control:</strong><br>
                            Define which users can access matters and specify their level of access.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Custom Access Settings:</strong><br>
                            Enable or disable permissions for Editing, Creation, Viewing, and Exporting
                            data on a per-matter basis.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Flexible Management:</strong><br>
                            Easily update rights when a team structure changes or when specific users need
                            restricted access to sensitive matters.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <h4>To assign or edit Matter Rights, you can follow the below steps:</h4>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Click on the <strong>Profile Placeholder</strong> icon and select
                            <strong>Rights</strong>.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            You will land on the <strong>Matter Rights</strong> tab by default.
                        </li>
                        <div class="case-page">
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/ADMIN_CONTROLS8.png" alt="addcase Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                        </div>



                        <li>
                            Click on the <strong>New Matter Rights</strong> button on the top right corner.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Firstly, select the user for whom you want the matter rights to be assigned.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Select the option of <strong>All Matter</strong> or choose particular matters
                            by clicking on <strong>Select Matters</strong>.
                        </li>

                        <div class="case-page">
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/ADMIN_CONTROLS9.png" alt="addcase Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                        </div>


                        <li>
                            Once the matters are selected, choose the rights you want to provide by
                            checking the boxes.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Click on <strong>Save</strong> button to update the changes.
                        </li>
                    </ul>




                </section>



