                    <p>
                        <h4>Action buttons on Matter list: </h4><br /> In the matter list, there are action buttons given under the ‘Action’ tab, which can be used to do various activities such as editing the matter, deleting the matter, etc. Please find the details of the buttons as below:
                        <div class="case-page">
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters9.png" alt="Matterlist Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                        </div>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Edit:</strong> The edit button is used to edit the details of the matter added such as Matter Name, Matter Description, Valuation of Suit, etc.</li>

                            <li><strong>Add User for Live Update:</strong> The option can be used to add the users for receiving live updates related to the matter. To know the process, please <strong>click here</strong>.</li>

                            <li><strong>Delete:</strong> The delete button is used to mark the case for deletion. The matters can’t be directly deleted and require the admin’s approval to permanently remove from the system. Once marked for deletion, the case will be highlighted as pink and will go to the Delete Request List.</li>

                            <li><strong>Archive:</strong> The archive button can be used to archive the matter. The matter can be archived in case it is disposed or not required in the Active Matter List. It will also not be a part of the reports downloaded from the Active Matter List; however, it will still be on live tracking and will utilize the case tracking quota. Once archived, the case will be added to the Archive List.</li>

                            <li><strong>Remove Live Tracking:</strong> The option is used to remove the matter from live tracking. Removing a matter from Live Tracking stops all automatic court updates, alerts, and notifications for that case. The matter’s timeline and cause list will no longer update, and any new orders or hearing dates must be added manually. While the matter remains available for reference, it becomes a static record rather than an actively tracked one. This action is recommended only for disposed or inactive cases.</li>

                            <li><strong>Add Live Tracking:</strong> The option will only be visible for cases which are litigation matters and are not on live tracking. It can be used to put the case on live tracking by entering the correct court and case details. To know the complete process, please <strong>click here</strong>.</li>

                            <li><strong>Add Notes:</strong> The email notes option will be visible only for the cases which are on live tracking. It can be used to add notes on cases, which will come along with the live update alert on email.</li>

                            <li><strong>Latest Order:</strong> The option allows you to directly access the most recent order uploaded on the court’s website for a particular matter.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>


                    <p>
                        <h4>Export to Excel or PDF:</h4><br />The system allows you to easily download the list of all your matters in an excel with just simple few steps:
                        <ul>


                            <li>Go to Matter List to open the entire list of all your active cases.</li>

                            <li>Now, you can apply your desired filters, if needed. For example, if you want to export only District court cases, you can filter the same from Court filter.</li>

                            <li>You can also add more columns to your view by selecting additional fields from the Customize option in the top right corner.</li>

                            <li>Once you have selected your desired filters and columns, please click on the <strong>Export</strong> button and select <strong>Export to Excel</strong> or <strong>Export to PDF</strong> as per your requirement.</li>

                            <li>You can download list of 500 matters in one excel when downloaded from Admin account and list of 200 matters in one excel when downloaded from User or Partner account.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <h4>Bulk Assign:</h4><br /> Bulk Assign feature can be used to assign multiple matters from one user to another user in a single action.<br />Please follow the below steps to bulk assign the matters:
                        <ul>
                            <div class="case-page">
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters10.png" alt="Matterlist Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>


                            <li>Go to the <strong>Matter List</strong> and click on the <strong>Bulk Assign</strong> option.</li>

                            <li>Select the user in the <strong>Assign From</strong> dropdown. The list of all cases assigned to that user will be displayed below.</li>

                            <li>Choose the cases that need to be assigned to another user from the displayed list. You can also apply filters on <strong>Court Type</strong> or search for specific cases using the <strong>matter name</strong>.</li>

                            <li>Once the cases are selected, choose the user in the <strong>Assign To</strong> list to whom the cases will be assigned.</li>

                            <li>After selecting the user, click on the <strong>Bulk Assign</strong> button to complete the reassignment of the selected matters.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <h4>Reset Custom Fields:</h4><br /> In addition to the default fields, any <strong>Custom Fields</strong> you have created can also be reset if required.To reset them, follow these steps:
                        <ul>


                            <li>Go to the <strong>Matter List</strong> to open the list of all your active cases.</li>

                            <li>Click on the <strong>Custom Field</strong> option and select <strong>Reset Custom Field</strong> from the dropdown.</li>

                            <li>Click on <strong>Confirm</strong> to reset the custom fields and the data entered in those fields.</li>

                            <li>After resetting the custom fields, you will not be able to see these fields in your default matter addition form or export them in Excel. However, the data entered earlier will still be stored under <strong>Custom Field History</strong>.</li>

                            <li>If you want to add new custom fields again in future, please follow the standard <strong>Custom Field creation</strong> process.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <h4>Custom Field History:</h4><br /> In case the Custom fields had some data stored and you have reset the fields, you can view the history by simply following the below steps:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Go to the <strong>Matter List</strong> to open the list of all your active cases.</li>

                            <li>Click on the <strong>Custom Field</strong> option and select the <strong>Custom Field History</strong> option.</li>

                            <li>In the popup that opens, select the <strong>version</strong> you want to view and click on <strong>Find</strong>.</li>

                            <div class="case-page">
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters11.png" alt="Matterlist Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>
                            <li>The displayed <strong>Custom Field History</strong> can also be exported into an Excel file by clicking on the <strong>Export</strong> button.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <h4>Adding User for Live Update:</h4><br /> You can add users to receive live updates for a specific case.
                        <ul>


                            <li>Click on the <strong>Add User for Live Update</strong> button to open the popup for user assignment.</li>
                            <div class="case-page">
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters12.png" alt="Matterlist Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>

                            <li>Click on the <strong>Select User</strong> dropdown, choose the users who need to be assigned to the matter, and then click on <strong>Save</strong>.</li>

                            <li>A list of all assigned users will be displayed below the dropdown. From this list, you can unassign any user by clicking on the <strong>delete</strong> button next to their name.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>





                    <p>
                        <h4>Viewing Case Details:</h4><br /> Under the <strong>Case Details</strong> column, you will see different briefcase icons that indicate the live tracking status and nature of the case.
                        <ul>

                            <li>A <strong>green briefcase icon</strong> represents that the case is on live tracking and the details are indexed from the court site.</li>

                            <li>An <strong>amber briefcase icon</strong> represents that the case has been put on live tracking, but the details are yet to be indexed from the court site.</li>

                            <li>A <strong>red briefcase icon</strong> represents that the case has been put on live tracking with incorrect details, and the case could not be found on the court site.</li>

                            <li>If there is <strong>no icon</strong> under the <strong>Case Details</strong> column, it means that the case is either a <strong>non-litigation matter</strong> or it has <strong>not been put on live tracking</strong> yet.</li>


                        </ul>
                    </p>
                    <p>When you click on the <strong>green briefcase icon</strong>, you can view live tracking details fetched from the court site, such as <strong>Next Hearing Date</strong>, <strong>Advocate</strong>, <strong>Case No.</strong>, etc.</p>
                    <div class="case-page">
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters13.png" alt="Matterlist Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <p>On the <strong>Case Details</strong> page, you can also view <strong>orders</strong>, <strong>causelist</strong>, set <strong>additional alerts</strong>, and perform other related actions.</p>

                    <p>
                        <strong>View, Download or Email Orders:  </strong>

                        <ul>
                            <li>Click on the View Orders button on the case details page to open the list of orders.</li>

                            <div class="case-page">
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters14.png" alt="Matterlist Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>

                            <li>To <strong>download</strong> the order to your system, click on the <strong>Download Order</strong> button.</li>

                            <li>To <strong>email</strong> the order, click on the <strong>Email Order</strong> button and enter the email address of the recipient in the popup. After entering the email address, click on <strong>Send</strong> to share the order copy as an email attachment.</li>


                            <div class="case-page">
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters15.png" alt="Matterlist Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>
                            <li>To <strong>view the order copy online</strong> without downloading it to your system, click on the <strong>View</strong> button to open the order copy.</li>


                        </ul>


                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <strong>Setting an Additional Alert:</strong><br /> You can set alerts for yourself or a client using either a <strong>specific date alert</strong> or a <strong>frequency-based alert</strong>.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        To understand and configure each option, please follow the steps below:
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Click on the Bell icon to open the additional alert option on the case details page.

                        <div class="case-page">
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters16.png" alt="Matterlist Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                        </div>


                    <p>
                        <strong>Specific Date Alert- </strong>
                        <div class="case-page">
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters17.png" alt="Matterlist Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                        </div>

                        <ul>
                            <li>Select the <strong>Date Based alert</strong> tab to set an alert for a specific date.</li>
                            <li>Choose the <strong>date</strong> on which you want the alert to be triggered.</li>
                            <li>In the <strong>Set Alert For</strong> column, select either <strong>Self</strong> or <strong>Client</strong> to specify the recipient of the alert.</li>
                            <li>If <strong>Client</strong> is selected, you will be prompted to enter the <strong>mobile number</strong> and <strong>email address</strong> to send the alert.</li>
                            <li>Once all the relevant details are entered, click on <strong>Set Alert</strong> to save the specific date alert.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>

                    <p>

                        <strong>Frequency-based Alert- </strong>
                        <div class="case-page">
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters18.png" alt="Matterlist Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                        </div>

                        <ul>
                            <li>Select the <strong>Hearing Day Based alert</strong> tab to set a frequency-based alert.</li>
                            <li>Select the <strong>Next Hearing Date</strong> around which you want to set the alert.</li>
                            <li>Choose the <strong>number of days</strong> and select whether the alert should be triggered <strong>Before hearing</strong> or <strong>After hearing</strong>.</li>
                            <li>In the <strong>Set Alert For</strong> column, select either <strong>Self</strong> or <strong>Client</strong> to specify the recipient of the alert.</li>
                            <li>If <strong>Client</strong> is selected, you will be prompted to enter the <strong>mobile number</strong> and <strong>email address</strong> to send the alert.</li>
                            <li>Once all the relevant details are entered, click on <strong>Set Alert</strong> to save the frequency-based alert.</li>
                        </ul>
                    <p>

                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <strong>Setting Manual Next Hearing Date:</strong><br /> If the next hearing date is not available on the court website, you can manually log the hearing date in Mykase to receive timely alerts.
                        <ul>
                            <li>To set a manual hearing date, click on the <strong>Add Manual Date</strong> option on the Case Details page.</li>

                            <div class="case-page">
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters19.png" alt="Matterlist Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>

                            <li>Select the <strong>Next Hearing Date</strong> from the date picker and click on <strong>Save</strong> to set the manual next hearing date.</li>
                            <div class="case-page">
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters20.png" alt="Matterlist Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>
                        </ul>
                    </p>




                </section>


                <section class="section case-page" id="matter-archive" style="display:none;">
                    <h2>Mattters- Archive Matter List</h2>
                    <div class="hr case-page"></div>

                    <p>
                        The archive matter list contains all cases that have been moved to archive from the active matter list. Archived matters are excluded from reports and Excel exports generated through the matter list. However, they remain on live tracking, and users will continue to receive update alerts for these cases.

                    </p>
                    <p>
                        For instance, if a case has been disposed of, you may not want it to appear in the active matter list or in reports. At the same time, it should not be permanently deleted from the system. In such situations, the case can be moved to the archive list.<br />
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        To view the Archive list, please follow the below steps:
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Click on Matter on the right panel and select Matter List.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Click on the Archive tab on the top left corner.
                            </li>
                            <div class="case-page">
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters21.png" alt="Matterlist Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>

                            <li>
                                In the list, you will see all the search, filters, action buttons, customize field and export options similar to the active matter list.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                In case any matter needs to be unarchived, you can simply click on the Unarchive button  and the matter will be added back to your Active Matter List.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class="section case-page" id="matter-delete" style="display:none;">
                    <h2>Mattters- Delete Request List</h2>
                    <div class="hr case-page"></div>

                    <p>
                        The <b>Delete Matters Request</b> List will only be visible in the admin’s account, from where the admin can take final action on the cases marked for deletion by the users. To do the same, please follow the below steps:
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        To view the Delete Request List, please follow the below steps:
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Click on <b>Matter</b> on the right panel and select Matter List.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Click on the <b>Delete Request</b> tab on the top left corner.
                            </li>
                            <div class="case-page">
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters22.png" alt="Matterlist Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>
                            <li>
                                You can view the details of the marked cases such as Deletion date, delete request by and the remark mentioned as the reason for deletion.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                From the list, the admin can search the request raised by specific user or directly search the matter through the Matter Name through the <b>Filters</b> option.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                For any specific matter, the admin can either delete it permanently from Mykase by clicking on the <strong>Delete button</strong>  or restore it permanently through the <strong>Restore button</strong>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                To delete or restore multiple cases at once, the admin can select the matters by clicking the checkboxes and once selected, click on <strong>Restore Selected</strong> or <strong>Bulk Delete</strong> option given on the top-right corner.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>

                </section>


                <section class="section case-page" id="matter-dash" style="display:none;">
                    <h2>Matter Dashboard</h2>
                    <div class="hr case-page"></div>

                    <p>
                        The Matter Dashboard serves as a complete notebook for an individual case, bringing together all related
                        information—documents, invoices, expenses, team members, and more—on a single page. You can access the
                        dashboard by clicking on any Matter Name in the Active Matter List.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        Once you click on the Matter name, the Matter Dashboard opens as shown below, displaying all tabs on a single page.
                    </p>

                    <div class="case-page">
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters23.png" alt="Matter Dashboard Overview"
                             class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <p>Below is the explanation of each tab along with its features and processes:</p>


                    <!-- COURT DETAILS -->
                    <h4>Court Details</h4>
                    <p>
                        The Court Details tab displays the same information available inside the Green Briefcase icon.
                        Click here to view details.
                    </p>


                    <!-- DOCUMENTS -->
                    <h4>Documents</h4>
                    <p>
                        The Documents section lets you view all document folders and files uploaded for the matter, along with
                        details such as date, file type, size, and description.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        To view a document or open a document folder, please click on the document or folder name respectively.

                    </p>
                    <p>
                        To search for any document, you can simply search the file from File Name <b>Search option</b>. In case you want to search for some specific text inside any document, then you can siwtch to <b>Free Text Search</b> option
                    </p>
                    <div class="case-page">
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters24.png" alt="Matter Dashboard Overview"
                             class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <h4>Create Folder</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Click on <b>Create Folder</b> (top-right corner).</li>
                        <li>Enter a folder name and click <b>Create</b>.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h4>Upload Documents</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Click on <b>Add Document</b> option and choose <b></b></li>
                        <li>A new popup will open where you can Drag/Drop the file or upload it from your system. </li>
                        <li>Mention the description of the file for your reference and click on the Attach Files button.</b>.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h4>Create New Document</h4>
                    <p>
                        Using the ‘Create New Document’ option, you can create an online Word document through Only Office and can collaborate with the team members on the same file.
                        <ul>
                            <li>Click on Add Document option and choose Create New Document.</li>
                            <li>Give a name to the file and click on the Create Document button to create the file. </li>
                            <li>Once created, the Only Office popup will open where you can now start adding/editing the content. You can also work on the same file with your team members in the track changes mode or Co-editing mode under Collaboration tab. </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
                    <div class="case-page">
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters25.png" alt="Matter Dashboard Overview"
                             class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <h4>Creating version of a document: </h4>
                    <p>
                        Mykase allows you to maintain up to 10 versions of the same document, ensuring that every update or revision is tracked without losing the original file. This helps in maintaining a clear record of changes and provides easy access to previous versions whenever required.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Please follow the below steps to create a version:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Click on <b>Check Out</b> button  under the Check Out Control column and the file will be downloaded into your system. </li>
                            <li>Once the file is downloaded the <b>Check Out</b> button will change into <b>Check in</b> button. </li>
                            <li>Update the downloaded file in your system and come back to the same document. </li>
                            <li>
                                Click on the <b>Checkin</b> button  and upload the updated file and a new version will be created for the document.

                            </li>
                        </ul>

                    </p>


                    <h4>Action Buttons in the Document Section</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><b>Share</b> – his option can be used to share the document with any user or client who is added to your Mykase and can access the portal.</li>
                        <li><b>Delete</b> – The delete button is used to mark the files for deletion. The documents can’t be directly deleted and require the admin’s approval to permanently remove from the system. Once marked for deletion, the documents will be highlighted as pink and will go to the Delete Request List under Admin account.</li>
                        <li><b>Edit Document</b> – The edit document option only appears for the word document which can be edited online.</li>
                        <li><b>Edit File Description</b> –The option is used to edit or add the file description.</li>
                        <li><b>Mark Confidential</b> –The Mark Confidential option can be used to mark the file as confidential. The team members who are assigned to this matter won’t be able to access the file, if marked as confidential.</li>
                        <li><b>Mark Non-confidential</b> – Once a document is marked as confidential, you can mark it as non-confidential using this option.</li>
                        <li><b>Version History</b> –The version history option is used to view and download the other version created of the document using the Check in and Check out option. </li>
                        <li><b>Upload Document to Cloud</b> – The upload document to cloud option is used to upload the document to your cloud such as Google Drive or Dropbox. </li>
                        <li><b>Document History</b> – The Document History can be used to view document history.</li>
                        <li><b>Download Original Version</b> – This option can be used to download the original document into your system</li>
                    </ul>


                    <!-- TASK -->
                    <h4>Task</h4>
                    <p>
                        The Task Tab helps you organize and manage all activities related to a matter. It allows you to create, assign, and track tasks, ensuring that important deadlines and responsibilities are not missed.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Under the task details, you can check all the task details such as task type, assigned by, assigned to, due date and status of the task. You can also filter the task based on these details.
                    </p>
                    <div class="case-page">
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters26.png" alt="Matter Dashboard Overview"
                             class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>
                    <p>
                        To assign a new task, please follow the below steps:
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Click on <b>Add Task</b>  option from the right panel and a popup will open.
                            </li>
                            <div class="case-page">
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters27.png" alt="Matter Dashboard Overview"
                                     class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>
                            <li>
                                While you are on the matter dashboard, the client and matter name will be auto fetched and added to the popup.
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                Now, add further details of the task like team members to whom the task will be assigned, task type, subject, due date, accept/reject by date, etc
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                Once you have added all the details, you can also add any attachments and click on <b>Assign task</b> button to assign the task.
                            </li>

                        </ul>
                    </p>

                    <!-- COMMUNICATION -->
                    <h4>Communication</h4>
                    <p>
                        The Communication Tab allows you to record and track all interactions related to a matter in one place. This ensures that important updates, discussions, and instructions are properly documented and easily accessible to the entire team.
                    </p>
                    <div class="case-page">
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters28.png" alt="Matter Dashboard Overview"
                             class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>
                    <p>
                        Under the Communication Tab, you can create communication threads to exchange and track messages related to the matter.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        To send message in the thread, you can follow the below steps:
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Click on the <b>Reply</b> button  against the thread created, which will open the complete thread popup.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                In the popup, you can send messages and even attach any supporting documents using the <b>Attachments</b> option.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
                    <div class="case-page">
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters29.png" alt="Matter Dashboard Overview"
                             class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>


                    <p>
                        To send a new communication, please follow the below steps:
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Click on the Add Communication option on the right panel and a popup will open.
                            </li>
                            <div class="case-page">
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters30.png" alt="Matter Dashboard Overview"
                                     class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>
                            <li>While you are on the matter dashboard, the client and matter name will be auto fetched and added to the popup. </li>


                            <li>
                                Once you have added all the details, you can also add any attachments and click on <b>Add Communication</b> button to send the communication.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>

                    <!-- CONTACTS -->
                    <h4>Contacts</h4>
                    <p>
                        The Contacts Tab displays all the contacts associated with a particular matter. You can view details such as name, role, designation, phone number, and email of the stakeholders linked to the case.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        To add a new contact, please follow the below steps:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Click on the <b>Add Contact</b>  option on the right panel and a popup will open.</li>
                            <li>To create a <b>company</b> contact, select the company tab.</li>
                            <div class="case-page">
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters31.png" alt="Matter Dashboard Overview"
                                     class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>

                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    Next, select the Company name from the dropdown or add a new Company Name
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    Enter the POC Name, Mobile Number, Email ID, Designation and Notes.
                                </li>

                                <li>
                                    Click on Add Contact button to save the contact.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                            <li>To create an individual contact, select the individual tab.</li>
                            <div class="case-page">
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters32.png" alt="Matter Dashboard Overview"
                                     class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    Now, add the POC Name, Mobile Number, Email ID, Designation and Notes.
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    Click on the Add Contact button to save the contact.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </ul>
                    </p>



                    <!-- FINANCES -->
                    <h4>Finances</h4>
                    <p>
                        The Finances Tab allows you to manage all financial aspects of a matter in one place. It brings together invoices, expenses, and time entries, ensuring accurate record-keeping and easy monitoring of costs associated with each matter.
                    </p>

                    <!-- INVOICES -->
                    <h4>Invoice</h4>
                    <p>Under the Invoice tab, you'll find all the details of the invoices created for the matter. This centralizes all generated invoices, making it easy to keep track of them. </p>
                    <div class="case-page">
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters33.png" alt="Matter Dashboard Overview"
                             class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <p>Below are some action buttons given for each invoice:</p>
                    <p></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><b>Pay Amount- </b>can be used to mark the payment status of the invoice and log the amount details.</li>
                        <li><b>Amend Invoice- </b>can be used to amend the invoice.  </li>
                        <li><b>Cancel Invoice- </b> can be used to cancel the invoice.  </li>
                        <li><b>Renew Invoice- </b>can be used to create a recurring invoice.  </li>
                        <li><b>Download Invoice- </b>can be used to download the invoice onto your system.  </li>
                        <li><b>Share Invoice- </b>can be used to share the invoice to the client directly from the system, provided the client has access to Mykase with the client credentials.</li>
                        <li><b>Share on Email- </b>can be used to mail the invoice to someone on an email with the remarks.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <p>
                        To create a new invoice, please follow the below steps:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Click <b>Create New Invoice</b>. button and a new form will open.</li>
                            <li>Now, you can choose the client details for whom you want to raise the invoice like Client Name, Client Address, Mobile Number, PAN and GST, etc. </li>
                            <li>Further you can add the Biller Details, Invoice Details such as Invoice Name, Invoice Date, Due Date, Particulars and Amount, etc. </li>
                            <li>Once all the details are added, please click on <b>Save Invoice</b> button to create the new invoice.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>


                    <!-- EXPENSE -->
                    <h4>Expense</h4>
                    <p>Under the Expense tab, you can have all the expenses related to the matter consolidated at one place</p>

                    <p>All the details such as Category, amount, payment mode, balance amount, description, etc. will be mentioned for each expense.   </p>
                    <div class="case-page">
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters34.png" alt="Matter Dashboard Overview"
                             class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <p>
                        Below are some action buttons given for each expense:
                        <ul>
                            <li><b>Edit Expense</b>can be used to edit the details of the expense.   </li>
                            <li><b>Delete Expense</b>can be used to delete the expense.  </li>
                            <li><b>Pay Amount</b>can be used to log the amount paid for the invoice.</li>
                        </ul>

                    </p>

                    <p>
                        To change the status of the expense, you can select the expenses from the checkbox and click on Change Status button.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        To create a new expense, please follow the below steps:
                        <ul>
                            <div class="case-page">
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters35.png" alt="Matter Dashboard Overview"
                                     class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>
                            <li>
                                Click on <b>Create New Expense</b> button  and a new popup will open.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Now, enter the details of expense such as Expense date, Expense type, Category, Amount, Receipt date, Due date, etc.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                You can also upload a receipt or invoice related to that expense.
                            </li>


                            <li>
                                Once all the details are added, you can click on <b>Add Expense</b> button to save the expense
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>





                    <!-- TIME ENTRY -->
                    <h4>Time Entry</h4>
                    <p>
                        In the time entry tab, you'll find detailed logs of the time you and your team members have recorded for tasks related to this matter.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        This information will help you track the time spent on the case, assisting lawyers in preparing invoices based on the time dedicated to the matter.To log a new Timy Entry, please follow the below steps:
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        To log a new Timy Entry, please follow the below steps:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Click <b>Time Entry</b> (top-right corner).</li>
                            <li>On the new page, click on the <b>Create Time Entry</b>button and a new popup will open. </li>
                            <li>Now, you can add the details in the popup such as Type and Matter Name.</li>
                            <li>Add the Task Type for which you are logging the time entry. You can also add a new task type if it is already not there in the list. </li>
                            <li>Then add the date of the task in the next column and you can also add a note along with an attachment.</li>
                            <li>
                                To log the time entry, you can either manually add the hr/min/sec or start the timer by pressing the play button  and once you have completed the task, you can click on pause button  to stop the timer.


                            </li>
                        </ul>

                    </p>



                    <!-- TEAM MEMBERS -->
                    <h4>Team Member</h4>
                    <p>
                        In the Team Member tab, you’ll find all the details of internal team members assigned to the matter, including their email addresses and phone numbers. This way, you won’t need to search elsewhere or scroll through your mobile directory for contact information.
                    </p>

                    <div class="case-page">
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Matters36.png" alt="Matter Dashboard Overview"
                             class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                </section>









                <section class="section case-page" id="cause-list" style="display:none;">
                    <h2>CauseList</h2>
                    <div class="hr case-page"></div>

                    <p>
                        As the Mykase tool provide you a personalized causelist of the matters added to your account, you can check the causelist by following the below steps:
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Click on Causelist option on the right panel to open the causelist screen
                            </li>
                            <div class="case-page">
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/CauseList0.png" alt="Revenue Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>
                            <li>
                                On the new page, you can select the type of forum i.e. Supreme Court, High Court, Tribunal, etc. for which you want to view the causelist
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Post selecting the forum, select the date and click on the Search button.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                The causelist of the applied filters will be generated accordingly and you can see the details such as Judge Name, Court Establishment, Item No., etc.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                To download the causelist, you can click on the Export button and select the option of Excel or PDF to download the list in the respective formats.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                To view the full causelist of the court, please click on the FullCauseList under the Action tab.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>



                </section>

                <section class="section case-page" id="calendar" style="display:none;">
                    <h2>Calendar</h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>
                    <p>
                        The calendar in Mykase helps you to keep track of all your hearings and orders related to all your cases. To access the calendar, please follow the below steps:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Click on <strong>Calendar</strong> option from the right panel from any page to get redirected to the calendar. </li>

                            <li>
                                <strong>Once the calendar opens</strong>, you can view a broad calendar, and an index of the same calendar color-coded for a better visualization on the left side.
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                In the calendar, you can click on the hyperlinked <b>Court Hearing or Order</b> to view more details.
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                You can also check other months by using the navigation arrows on the top of the calendar.
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                Once clicked on <b>Court Hearing</b>, a popup will open including all the cases listed for that date.
                            </li>
                            <div>
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Calendar1.png" alt="Documents Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>
                            <li>
                                In the popup, you can use the below buttons to perform various actions:
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        <b>Send Alert button</b> - can be used to trigger an alert for all the listed cases to the relevant team members assigned to the cases
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <strong>Download PDF button</strong> - can be used to download a PDF of the complete list of cases.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <strong>Download Excel button</strong> - can be used to download the excel of the complete list of cases.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <strong>Send Email button</strong> - can be used to send the list of all the cases to your colleague, client, advocate or even yourself through email directly from the system
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                Once clicked on Order, a popup will open including all the cases where an order is updated for that date.
                            </li>
                            <div>
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Calendar2.png" alt="Documents Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>


                            <li>Inside the popup, you can use the below buttons to perform various actions:</li>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <b>Download PDF button</b> - can be used to download a PDF of the complete list of cases.
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <b> Download Excel button</b> - can be used to download the excel of the complete list of cases.
                                </li>
                                <li><b>Send Email button</b> - can be used to send the list of all the cases to your colleague, client, advocate or even yourself through email directly from the system</li>
                                <li><b>Download Order</b> - can be used to download the order copy on your system </li>
                            </ul>


                            <li>The calendar can also be synced with your Google calendar, which will reflect all your hearings in your Google calendar and help you prevent missing out on any hearing. To sync your calendar with your Google calendar, please follow the below steps: </li>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    Click on the Google Calendar Sync button on the calendar page, which will open a new browser popup, allowing you to choose your Gmail
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    Click on the account that you want to sync and click on Continue and check all the access options and continue to complete the sync process.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </ul>
                    </p>

                </section>





                <section class="section case-page" id="documents" style="display:none;">
                    <h2>Documents</h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>
                    <p>
                        In the Document Management tab, you will find a repository for all documents associated with your cases. Whenever a new matter is added, a corresponding folder is automatically created under the case name.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        In the Documents section, you can search for any document by its name or even perform a content-based search within documents, through the below options:
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <strong>
                                    File Name Search
                                </strong>
                                - If you know the name of the document, simply enter it in the search bar to quickly locate the file.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>
                                    Free Text Search
                                </strong>
                                - This option allows you to search within the content of documents. For example, if you're looking for documents that contain the phrase criminal proceedings, go to the Documents section, select Free Text Search from the dropdown, enter the keyword and click Search. The system will return all documents where the specified keyword appears in the content.
                            </li>

                            <div>
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Documents0.png" alt="Documents Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>
                        </ul>

                    </p>

                    <h4>Create a New Folder:</h4>
                    <p>
                        The Create Folder option allows you to organize your documents by creating structured folders within the Document Section. This helps in categorizing files based on matters, document types, or teams, making it easier to manage and retrieve documents efficiently. You can also create folders inside the folders.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        To create a folder, follow these steps:
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Go to the document section and click on <b>+ Create New Folder</b> button on the top right.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                In the popup, enter the name of the folder and click on <b>Add New Folder</b> to save the folder.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        <div>
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Documents1.png" alt="Documents Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                        </div>
                    </p>


                    <h4>Upload a Document: </h4>



                    <p>
                        To upload a new document, please follow the below steps:<br />
                        <div>
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Documents2.png" alt="Documents Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                        </div>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Open the destination folder where you want to upload the file.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Click on <b>Add Document</b> button on the top right.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                From the dropdown, select <b>Upload Document</b>.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Inside the popup, you can click on <b> Click to upload</b> or drag and drop the file needed to be uploaded.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                You can also mention the File description, if needed and click on Upload <b>Document</b> button to save the document in your repository.
                            </li>
                        </ul>

                    </p>




                    <h4>Create a new Document: </h4>
                    <p>
                        The Create New Document feature allows users to generate documents directly within the platform without needing to upload them from external sources. This is useful for drafting templates, notices, reports, or any matter-related documentation in real time.
                    </p>


                    <p>
                        To create a new document, follow these steps: <br />

                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Click on <b>Add Document</b> option and choose <b>Create New Document</b>.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Give a name to the file and click on the <b>Create Document</b> button to create the file.
                            </li>
                            <div>
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Documents3.png" alt="Documents Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>
                            <li>
                                Once the document is created, it will open through the <b>Only Office</b> window.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <b>Use the built-in editor</b> to draft or type your content. The newly created document can then be shared and edited. Also, track changes and collaboration can be done so the team can work on the same file.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                To edit the same document, click on the <b>three-dot</b> menu and choose <b>Edit Document.</b>.
                            </li>
                        </ul>

                    </p>



                    <h4>Move Document: </h4>
                    <p>
                        The <b>Move Document</b> feature allows users to relocate a file or document from one folder to another within the Document Section.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        To move a document, follow these steps: <br />

                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Go to the <b>Document Section</b> and locate the document you want to move.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Select the document(s) using the <b>checkbox</b> next to each file.
                            </li>
                            <div>
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Documents4.png" alt="Move Document" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>
                            <li>
                                Click on the <b>Add Document</b> button and choose <b>Move Document</b>.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                A dialog box will appear—select the destination folder from the folder list.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Click on <b>Move</b> to complete the action.
                            </li>
                        </ul>


                    </p>


                    <h4>Creating Version of a Document: </h4>
                    <p>
                        Mykase allows you to maintain up to <b>10 versions</b>of the same document, ensuring that every update or revision is tracked without losing the original file. This helps in maintaining a clear record of changes and provides easy access to previous versions whenever required.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        Please follow the below steps to create a version:  <br />

                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Click on the <b>Check Out</b> button under the Check Out Control column and the file will be downloaded into your system.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                The document will be downloaded to your system, and the <b>Check Out</b> button will change to <b>Check In</b>.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Update the downloaded file in your system and come back to the same document.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Click on the <b>Check In</b> button and upload the updated file and a new version will be created for the document.
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                A new version of the document will be created automatically.
                            </li>
                        </ul>


                    </p>


                    <h4>Action Buttons in the Document Section: </h4>


                    <p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <b>Share</b> – This option can be used to share the document with any user or client who is added to your Mykase and can access the portal.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <b>Delete</b> –The delete button is used to mark the files for deletion. The documents can’t be directly deleted and require the admin’s approval to permanently remove from the system. Once marked for deletion, the documents will be highlighted as pink and will go to the Delete Request List under Admin account.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <b>Edit Document</b> – The edit document option only appears for the word document which can be edited online.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <b>Edit File Description</b> – he option is used to edit or add the file description.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <b>Mark Confidential</b> – The Mark Confidential option can be used to mark the file as confidential. The team members who are assigned to this matter won’t be able to access the file, if marked as confidential.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <b>Mark Non-Confidential</b> – Once a document is marked as confidential, you can mark it as non-confidential using this option.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <b>Version History</b> – The version history option is used to view and download the other version created of the document using the Check in and Check out option.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <b>Upload Document to Cloud</b> – The upload document to cloud option is used to upload the document to your cloud such as Google Drive or Dropbox.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <b>Document History</b> – The Document History can be used to view document history.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <b>Download Original Version</b> – This option can be used to download the original document into your system.
                            </li>
                        </ul>


                    </p>


                    <h4>Shared Documents: </h4>
                    <p>
                        The <b>Shared Documents</b> section displays all the documents and folders that have been shared with you by other users. It provides a consolidated view of shared content, along with the specific access rights granted to you—such as view, download, or edit permissions.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        To view shared documents, follow these steps: <br />

                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Navigate to the <b>Documents Section</b> from the left menu and click on the Shared Documents tab.
                            </li>

                        </ul>
                        <div>
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Documents5.png" alt="Shared Documents" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                        </div>


                    </p>


                    <h4>Check Out List: </h4>
                    <p>
                        The <b>Check-Out List</b> section displays all the documents that have currently been checked out for editing. It helps you keep track of files that are temporarily locked for updates, ensuring that no other users make changes to them during that period.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                If a document is checked out by you, the option to <b>Check In</b> will appear on the same page, allowing you to upload the updated version once edits are complete.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                If a document is checked out by someone else, it will show as In Use to you, indicating that it cannot be checked out again until the other user checks it back in.
                            </li>
                        </ul>

                        <div>
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Documents6.png" alt="Check Out List" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                        </div>
                    </p>


                    <h4>Delete Request: </h4>
                    <p>
                        The <b>Delete Request List</b> s a dedicated section visible only to admin, where all document deletion requests submitted by users are displayed for review. This ensures that no file is permanently removed without proper authorization.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        The admin can permanently delete any document by following below steps:
                        <div>
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Documents7.png" alt="Delete Request List" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                        </div>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        From the Delete Request List, the admin can delete or restore the matters by following the below steps:
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                You can click on <b>Delete</b> button to delete the marked documents.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                To restore a document back into the repository, click on the <b>Restore</b> button .
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                To bulk delete the documents, please select the documents from the checkbox and click on <b> Delete Selected</b> button.
                            </li>
                        </ul>


                    </p>

                </section>


                <section class="section case-page" id="reports" style="display:none;">
                    <h2>Reports </h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>
                    <p>
                        The Reports section provides a consolidated view of data across matters, helping you track performance, monitor progress, and analyze key metrics. It allows you to generate customized reports for better insights and decision-making.
                        <div>
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Reports1.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                        </div>
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        You can generate reports for:
                        <ol>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Matter List</strong> -You can generate reports for matters added by a specific user or assigned to a particular user. These reports can be filtered by matter status and court name. You also have the option to customize the fields according to your report requirements. To download the report, click on the Download Report button.

                            </li>
                            <div class="case-page">
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Reports2.png" alt="Pro-Active Alerts Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Billing</strong> - Under the billing section, you can generate the reports of your invoices and expenses:
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        <strong>Invoice</strong>
                                        You can generate reports for your invoices, and these reports can be filtered by Client Name, Matter Name & Invoice Status. You also have the option to customize the fields according to your report requirements. To download the report, click on the action selected button: export to PDF or export to Excel.
                                    </li>
                                    <div class="case-page">
                                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Reports4.png" alt="Pro-Active Alerts Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                                    </div>

                                    <li>
                                        <strong>Expense Created</strong>
                                        You can generate reports for your expenses, and these reports can be filtered by Client Name, Matter Name, Category & Expense Type. You also have the option to customize the fields according to your report requirements. To download the report, click on the action selected button: export to PDF or export to Excel.
                                    </li>

                                    <div class="case-page">
                                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Reports5.png" alt="Pro-Active Alerts Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                                    </div>

                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Time Entry- </strong>
                                - You can generate reports for your tasks & these reports can be filtered by User name, Client & Matter Name . You also have the option to customize the fields according to your report requirements. To download the report, click on the action selected button: export to PDF or export to Excel.
                            </li>

                            <div class="case-page">
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Reports6.png" alt="Pro-Active Alerts Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>

                            <li><strong>Task-</strong>You can generate reports for your tasks & these reports can be filtered by User name, Client & Matter Name . You also have the option to customize the fields according to your report requirements. To download the report, click on the action selected button: export to PDF or export to Excel.</li>
                            <div class="case-page">
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Reports7.png" alt="Pro-Active Alerts Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Workspace Reports-</strong>Under workspace reports, you can extract the report of user activity and user list.
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        <strong>
                                            User Activity-
                                        </strong>
                                        You can generate reports to track user activity, including details such as login and logout times, matter creation and editing, document uploads, and document modifications. Additionally, you can customize the fields to meet your specific reporting needs. To download the report, click the action button and select either "Export to PDF" or "Export to Excel."
                                    </li>
                                    <div class="case-page">
                                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Reports8.png" alt="Pro-Active Alerts Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                                    </div>

                                    <li>
                                        <strong>
                                            Users report-
                                        </strong>
                                        You can generate reports to access your user list & these can be filtered by User Type, their designation & department. You also have the option to customize the fields according to your report requirements. To download the report, click on the action selected button: export to PDF or export to Excel.
                                    </li>
                                    <div class="case-page">
                                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Reports9.png" alt="Pro-Active Alerts Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                                    </div>
                                </ul>

                            </li>

                            <li>
                                <strong>
                                    Contacts-
                                </strong>
                                You can generate reports for your contact list, which can be filtered by contact type—Vendor, Prospect, or Client. Additionally, you can refine your search by company name.  To download the report, click on the action selected button: export to PDF or export to Excel.
                            </li>
                            <div class="case-page">
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Reports10.png" alt="Pro-Active Alerts Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>
                        </ol>
                    </p>






                </section>





                <section class="section case-page" id="hub-communication" style="display:none;">
                    <h2>Hub-Communication</h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>
                    <p>
                        The Hub Section in Mykase acts as a central collaboration and information center which brings together all essential tools for communication, contact management, and knowledge sharing — ensuring that your entire team stays informed, connected, and organized.


                    </p>
                    <p>
                        The Hub consists of three key components: Communication, Contacts, and Knowledge. Each plays a crucial role in managing the day-to-day coordination and reference material related to a matter.
                    </p>
                    <h4>
                        Communication
                    </h4>
                    <p>
                        The Communication Tab is a central repository of all messages that allows team members to create and maintain discussion threads specific to a matter. Instead of relying on external emails or chats, you can exchange messages directly within the platform — keeping all correspondence contextually linked to the relevant case.

                    </p>
                    @*<img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/AddComm.png">*@

                    <p>
                        To send a new communication, please follow the below steps:

                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Click on the <b>Add Communication</b> option on the right panel and a popup will open.
                            </li>
                            <div>
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserManual/tools.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>

                            <li>
                                Enter the matter name to link the communication with that matter. In case the matter is mapped with a particular client, you can type three letters of the Client contact and select from the option provided.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Now, enter the Subject and the Message you want to send to your team members.
                            </li>


                            <li>
                                Once the details are added, select the team members, add any attachments and click on <b>Add Communication</b> button to send the communication.

                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        Under the communication tab, you apply date filters, search based on communication notes or matter name and view or reply to any communication thread.
                    </p>



                    <p>
                        To send message in the thread, you can follow the below steps:
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Click on the <b>Reply </b> button against the thread created, which will open the complete thread popup.
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                In the popup, you can send messages and even attach any supporting documents using the <b>Attachments</b> option.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>

                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/comm2.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>






                </section>





                <section class="section case-page" id="hub-contacts" style="display:none;">
                    <h2>Hub-Contacts</h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>
                    <p>
                        The Contacts Tab displays a consolidated list of all the contacts created. It provides quick access to essential details such as names, roles, organizations, and contact information

                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Under the contacts tab, you can view the list of All contacts, Company contacts and Individual contacts simply by toggling between the tabs.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        To view more information, you can select the required columns from the <b>Customize option</b> in the Contact list and the columns will be temporarily added in the list.
                    </p>
                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/contact1.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <h4>Creation of Contact through Right Panel: </h4>

                    <p>
                        To add a new contact, please follow the below steps:

                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Click on the <b>Add Contact</b> option on the right panel and a popup will open.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                To create a company contact, select the company tab.
                            </li>
                            <div>
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/contact2.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>

                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    Next, select the Company name from the dropdown or add a new Company Name
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    Enter the POC Name, Mobile Number, Email ID, Designation and Notes.
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    Click on <b>Add Contact</b> button to save the contact.
                                </li>
                            </ul>

                            <li>
                                To create an individual contact, select the individual tab.
                                <div>
                                    <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/contact3.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                                </div>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        Now, add the POC Name, Mobile Number, Email ID, Designation and Notes.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        Click on the <b>Add Contact</b> button to save the contact.
                                    </li>

                                </ul>
                            </li>



                        </ul>
                    </p>

                    <h4>
                        Creation of Contact through Long Form:
                    </h4>

                    <p>
                        To create a new contact through long form, please follow the below steps:

                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Click on the <b>Create Contact</b> button on the top-right in the Contact list.
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                In the form that opens, firstly select the category of the contact as individual or company
                            </li>
                            <div>
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/contact4.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>

                            <li>Now, enter the further details such as Name, Designation, Address, Contact Details, Aadhar, PAN, GST, etc.</li>
                            <li>Once all the details are added, click on the Save button to create the contact. </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>



                    <p>
                        You can also share these contacts with anyone through email by following the below steps:
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Click on the Share button on the top-right of the contacts module.
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                In the popup, enter the Email ID on which you want to send the contact list and click on Send button.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        To download the excel or PDF of the contact list, you can click on Share button on the top-right corner of the Contact list.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        You can also save and view multiple client address by following the below steps:

                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Click on the <b>Client Multiple Address</b> button in the Contact List.
                                <div>
                                    <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/contact5.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                                </div>
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                On the screen that opens, you can see the option to add multiple addresses in the top half of the screen.


                                <div>
                                    <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/contact6.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                                </div>
                            </li>


                            <li>
                                You can select the client for which you want to add the multiple address and then add the further details like the State, City, Pincode, Address, etc.
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                Once all the details are added, you can click on Save button to add the details.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                In the bottom half of the screen, you will be able to see all the added addresses, which you can edit or delete from there.
                            </li>

                        </ul>

                    </p>


                    <h4>
                        Client/Counsel Credentials:
                    </h4>
                    <p>
                        The Client/Counsel Portals in Mykase are secure, dedicated spaces that allow external stakeholders — such as clients and external counsels — to collaborate directly on their assigned matters on the tool. These portals are designed to provide transparency, reduce manual communication, and enable real-time access to matter updates, documents, and tasks.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        By offering controlled access, the portals ensure that external users can view and act only on the information relevant to them, maintaining complete data security and confidentiality.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        To create a client/counsel portal, please follow the below steps:
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Firstly, you need to create a contact using the right panel or long form.
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                In the contact list, click on the <b> Add Credentials</b> button under the Status tab for the contact where you want to provide the portal.
                            </li>
                            <div>
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/contact7.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>

                            <li>
                                In the popup, create a new User ID and password, using which the client or counsel can login into their portal.
                            </li>
                            <div>
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/conatct8.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>
                        </ul>
                    </p>



                </section>


                <section class="section case-page" id="hub-knowledge" style="display:none;">
                    <h2>Hub-Knowledge</h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>
                    <p>
                        The <b>Knowledge Section</b> serves as a central repository where you can store, organize, and access all legal research materials, reference documents, templates, and other knowledge resources within the platform. It helps your team maintain consistency in drafting and ensures quick access to important precedents or formats when needed.
                    </p>
                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/know1.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>
                    <p>
                        Under the knowledge section, you can see all the documents added by you or shared with you.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        To create a new folder in the Knowledge section, please follow the below steps:
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Click on the <b>Add New Folder</b> button<img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/addnewfolder.png"> on the top right corner of the Knowledge section.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Enter the folder name and click on  <b>Add New Folder</b> button to save the folder.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        To upload a new document, please follow the below steps:
                        <div>
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/know3.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                        </div>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Click on the <b>Upload Document</b> button<img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/uploaddocu.png"> on the top right corner of the Knowledge section.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                In the popup, upload the document from your local system.
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                Now, add the Title, Category, Author, Date, Source and Description.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Click on <b>Upload Document</b> button to finally save the document in the Knowledge section.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>


                    <h4>
                        Action buttons in the Knowledge section:
                    </h4>

                    <p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><b>View Document</b><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/tview.png">- The View Document button is used to view open the document in a preview popup. </li>
                            <li><b>Delete Document</b><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/tdel.png">- The Delete Document button is used to delete the document from the knowledge section. It is only visible to the creator of the file.</li>

                            <li><b>Download Document </b><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/do.png">- The Download Document button is used to download the file into your system locally.  </li>



                            <li>
                                <b>Document Permission</b><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/uploaddocu.png">- Using the Document Permission button, you can share the document with your team members and manage view or download rights as well.

                                <div>
                                    <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/down.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                                </div>
                                <p>
                                    To do the same, please follow the below steps:

                                    <ul>
                                        <li>
                                            Click on the Share button and a popup will open.
                                        </li>


                                        <li>
                                            Select the user for which the rights have to be provided.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            Select the checkboxes for giving permission and click on <b>Share Document</b> button to share the document.
                                        </li>



                                    </ul>
                                </p>

                            </li>

                            <li>
                                <b>Email Document</b><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/email.png"> -The Email Document can be used to share the document externally on email. To share the document on email, click on the button, enter the desired email id in the popup and click on <b>Share Document</b> button.
                            </li>
                        </ul>















                    </p>


                    <p>
                        Also, the list of all documents uploaded in the knowledge section can be downloaded into PDF by clicking on the Export button<img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/export.png"> .
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        You can also mark or unmark any document as your favourite by simply selecting or unselecting the checkbox under the Favourite column respectively.
                    </p>
                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/know3.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>



                    <p>
                        All the document marked as favourite can be viewed under the <b>Pinned File tab</b>.
                    </p>
                </section>







                <section class="section case-page" id="task" style="display:none;">
                    <h2>Task</h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>
                    <p>
                        The Task Section is designed to help you manage and track all activities linked to your matters. It provides a centralized space where you can assign responsibilities, set deadlines, and monitor progress, ensuring that no important task is overlooked. <br>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        To assign a new task, please follow the below steps:
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Click on <b>Add Task </b><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/AddTask.png"> option from the right panel and a popup will open.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                You can select the client details and matter name for which you want to assign the task.
                            </li>
                            <div>
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Task1.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>

                            <li>
                                Now, add further details of the task like team members to whom the task will be assigned, task type, subject, due date, accept/reject by date, etc
                            </li>

                            <li>

                                Once you have added all the details, you can also add any attachments and click on <b>Assign task</b> button to assign the task.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>

                    <h4>
                        New Task Request:
                    </h4>
                    <p>
                        The New Task Request Tab lists all tasks that have been assigned to you but are awaiting your acceptance. From this tab you can review each assignment and either Accept it (so it becomes an active task in your My Task Section) or Reject it (so it returns to the assigner).
                    </p>
                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Task2.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <h4>Accept a task:</h4>
                    <p>
                        To accept a task, please follow the below steps:
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Click on the <b>Accept Button</b><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Accept.png"> under the Take Action tab.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                In the popup displayed, set your own deadline apart from the due date provided by the assigner.
                            </li>
                            <div>
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Task3.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>

                            <li>
                                Finally, click on the <b>Accept Task</b> button in the popup.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>


                    <h4>Reject a Task:</h4>
                    <p>
                        To reject a task, please follow the below steps:
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Click on the <b>Reject button </b><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Reject.png"> under the Take Action tab.
                            </li>
                            <div>
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Task4.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>


                            <li>
                                In the popup, mention the reason of the rejection and click on <b>Reject Task</b> button.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        You can also view the document attached by the assigner by clicking on the <b>Document button</b><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/addnewfolder.png"> under the Take Action tab.
                    </p>


                    <h4>My Task:</h4>
                    <p>
                        The <b>My Task Section</b> provides a consolidated view of all tasks that involve you, either as an assignee (tasks assigned to you) or as an <b>assigner</b> (tasks you created and that have been accepted by others). This ensures you can easily track both your own responsibilities and the progress of tasks you have delegated.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        In the My Task section, you can filter the tasks based on task type, assigned by, <b>assigned</b> to or status.

                        <div>
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Task5.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                        </div>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                For any pending task which is assigned to you, you can mark them as completed by clicking on the <b>Complete button</b> under the action tab.
                            </li>



                            <li>
                                You can also attach any supporting document before completing any task by clicking on the three-dot menu and choosing <b>Attachment option</b> under the action tab.
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                For the pending task assigned to you or assigned by you, you can also set an additional alert before the due date, by following the below steps:
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        Click on the three-dot menu and choose <b>Set Alert</b> option under the action tab.
                                    </li>

                                    <li>
                                        In the popup, you can either select the alert date or set a frequency alert before the due date
                                    </li>
                                    <div>
                                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Task6.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                                    </div>
                                    <li>
                                        Further, you can select whether you want to set the reminder for the Assignee, self or both. In case, you are setting an alert on a task assigned to you by someone, you can set the alert only for yourself.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        You can add some remark as well before clicking on <b>Set Alert</b> button to create the alert.
                                    </li>
                                </ul>

                            </li>
                            For the documents, you can click on the Documents button under the action tab, and a popup will open where you will get two options:
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <strong>Attached Doc-</strong>Under this section, you can see all the documents attached by the assignee before completing the task.
                                </li>

                                <li>
                                    <strong>Assigned Doc-</strong>Under this section, you can see all the documents attached by the assigner while assigning the task.
                                </li>
                            </ul>

                        </ul>
                    </p>




                    <h3>Overdue:</h3>
                    <p>
                        The Overdue Section displays all tasks that have passed their due date but remain incomplete. It includes both:
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Tasks Assigned to You –</strong>tasks you accepted but did not complete on time
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Tasks Assigned by You –</strong>tasks you created for others that were accepted but not finished within the deadline.
                            </li>




                        </ul>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        If the task is assigned to you, the below actions can be taken on the tasks:

                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                You can mark the task as completed by clicking on the <b>Complete button</b><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Accept.png"> under the action tab.
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                You can reject the overdue task by clicking on the <b> Reject button</b><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Reject.png"> under the action tab.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Attach Documents by clicking on the three-dot menu and selecting <b>Attach Document</b><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/attachment.png"> option under the action tab.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                By clicking on <b>Document Folder</b> button to check the documents attached with the task.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        If the task is assigned by you to someone else, the below actions can be taken on the tasks:

                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                You can send a reminder to the <b>assignee</b> by clicking on the <b>Alert</b> button under the action tab.
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                By clicking on <b>Document Folder</b> button to check the documents attached with the task.
                            </li>

                        </ul>
                    </p>


                </section>




                <section class="section case-page" id="tools-compare-documents">
                    <h2>Tools- Compare Documents</h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>

                    <p>
                        The <b>Tools</b> section in <b>Mykase</b> offers a suite of productivity utilities
                        designed to streamline day-to-day legal operations and enhance document accuracy,
                        accessibility, and compliance.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        These tools assist users in comparing documents, detecting conflicts, managing
                        scanned files, integrating cloud storage, and digitally signing documents — all
                        within a secure environment.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        To access the <b>Tools</b> section, click on the <b>Tools </b><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/toolss.png"> option available on
                        the right panel.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        Below are the tools available under this section.
                    </p>


                    <h4>Compare Documents</h4>

                    <p>
                        The <b>Compare Documents</b> feature allows you to instantly identify changes,
                        discrepancies, or modifications between two versions of a document.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        It highlights insertions, deletions, and text differences, making it easier to
                        review edits and maintain version control.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        This feature is ideal for contract review, agreement comparison, and document vetting.
                    </p>

                    <p><b>To compare any documents, please follow the steps below:</b></p>
                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/tools1.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Click on the <b>Tools</b> section and select <b>Compare Documents</b>.</li>
                        <li>
                            On the Compare Documents tab, upload the <b>Primary</b> file and
                            <b>Secondary</b> file through your local drive or Mykase document repository.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Once uploaded, add the <b>File Name</b> and you can also set an
                            <b>Expiry Date</b> by when the documents will be saved in history.
                        </li>
                        <li>Select the <b>Save</b> checkbox to save the documents in history.</li>
                        <li>Click on the <b>Compare Document</b><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/comparedoc.png"> button to perform the comparison.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <p>
                        Under the <b>History</b> section, you can view all previously compared documents
                        that were saved.
                    </p>
                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/tools2.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>


                </section>



                <section class="section case-page" id="tools-conflict-search">
                    <h2>Tools- Conflict Search</h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>

                    <p>
                        The <b>Conflict Search</b> tool helps you detect potential conflicts of interest
                        across cases, matters, and clients.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        It scans through your existing database to identify any overlapping parties,
                        counsels, or subject matters, ensuring ethical compliance before taking on a new case.
                    </p>

                    <p><b>To use Conflict Search, please follow the steps below:</b></p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>Click on the <b>Tools</b> section and select <b>Conflict Search</b>.</li>
                        <li>
                            In the search bar, enter the name of the <b>client</b>, <b>opposing party</b>,
                            <b>counsel</b>, or any other related keyword you want to check for conflicts.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Choose the desired scope by selecting the type — you can search across
                            <b>all matters</b>, <b>clients</b>, <b>petitioner</b>, or <b>respondent</b>.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Click on the <b>Search</b> button to view the results. The system will display
                            all existing records that match your search criteria.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <p>
                        You can review details such as matter name, client name, case type, and assigned
                        user to assess any possible conflict.
                    </p>
                </section>




                <section class="section case-page" id="tools-ocr">
                    <h2>Tools- OCR(Optical Character Recognition)</h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>

                    <p>
                        <b>OCR</b> converts scanned legal documents and PDFs into searchable and editable text.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        This helps you quickly locate information within scanned files and reuse content
                        in drafting or reporting.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        It eliminates the need for manual data entry and improves document accessibility.
                    </p>
                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/tools3.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <p>
                        To run <b>OCR</b> on any document, please follow the steps below:
                    </p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>Go to the <b>Tools</b> section and select <b>OCR</b>.</li>
                        <li>
                            Upload the scanned document or PDF you want to convert.
                            You can also select a document from <b>Mykase Repository</b>
                            by clicking on <b>Mykase Drive</b>.
                        </li>
                        <li>Click on the <b>Convert Document</b> button to initiate the process.</li>
                        <li>
                            Once completed, review the extracted text for accuracy and
                            download the editable version, print it directly, or email it from the system.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </section>



                <section class="section case-page" id="tools-cloud-integration">
                    <h2>Tools- Cloud Integration</h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>

                    <p>
                        With <b>Cloud Integration</b>, you can securely sync, store, and access your case
                        files anytime, from anywhere.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        It ensures seamless connectivity between your desktop and cloud storage,
                        providing real-time access and backups for all critical legal documents.
                    </p>

                    <h4>OneDrive Integration</h4>


                    <p>
                        The <b>OneDrive Integration</b> lets users securely link their Microsoft account
                        and access documents stored on OneDrive.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <b>Steps to integrate OneDrive:</b>
                    </p>
                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/tools4.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Navigate to <b>Tools</b> and select <b>Cloud Integration</b>.</li>
                        <li>Select the <b>OneDrive</b> tab under the cloud integration section.</li>
                        <li>Click on the <b>Connect Now </b><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/connectnow.png"> button.</li>
                        <li>
                            On the new page, sign in to your Microsoft Outlook account
                            to complete the integration.
                        </li>
                    </ul>




                    <!-- ================= OneDrive ================= -->
                    <!-- ================= Dropbox ================= -->
                    <!-- ================= Dropbox ================= -->

                    <h4>Dropbox Integration</h4>


                    <p>
                        The <b>Dropbox Integration</b> enables seamless access to documents stored
                        on Dropbox, ensuring all case-related files remain organized and centralized.
                    </p>

                    <p><b>Steps to integrate Dropbox Drive:</b></p>
                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/tools5.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Navigate to <b>Tools</b> and select <b>Cloud Integration</b>.</li>
                        <li>Select the <b>Dropbox</b> tab under the cloud integration section.</li>
                        <li>Click on the <b>Connect Now </b><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/connectnow.png"> button.</li>
                        <li>
                            On the new page, sign in to your Dropbox account
                            to complete the integration.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <!-- ================= Google Drive ================= -->

                    <h4>Google Drive Integration</h4>

                    <p>
                        Connecting <b>Google Drive</b> allows you to access all your Drive files
                        directly within <b>Mykase</b>.
                    </p>

                    <p><b>Steps to integrate Google Drive:</b></p>
                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/tools6.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Navigate to <b>Tools</b> and select <b>Cloud Integration</b>.</li>
                        <li>Select the <b>Google Drive</b> tab under the cloud integration section.</li>
                        <li>Click on the <b>Connect Now </b><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/connectnow.png"> button.</li>
                        <li>
                            On the new page, sign in to your Google account
                            to complete the integration.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </section>


                <section class="section case-page" id="tools-digital-signature">
                    <h2>Tools- Digital Signature</h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>

                    <p>
                        The <b>Digital Signature</b> feature allows users to sign documents electronically
                        in a secure, verifiable, and legally compliant manner.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        It eliminates the need for physical signatures, speeds up approval processes,
                        and ensures authenticity and integrity of signed files.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        To use the <b>Digital Signature</b> process, please follow the steps below:
                    </p>

                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/tools7.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Go to the <b>Tools</b> section and select <b>Digital Signature</b>.</li>
                        <li>
                            Upload the document you wish to sign by clicking on the
                            <b>Local Drive</b> button or upload it from <b>Mykase Drive</b>.
                        </li>
                        <li>Click on the <b>Process</b> button to process the file.</li>
                        <li>
                            Select the process and page through which you want to sign the document,
                            such as <b>DSC Signature</b>, <b>Aadhaar Signature</b>, or <b>E-Signature</b>.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Once the signature type and page are selected, click on the
                            <b>Confirm</b> button to get redirected to the signature gateway.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Add your signature using your registered digital certificate or
                            preconfigured signing method.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            After signing, download the digitally signed document from
                            <b>Mykase Previous Signed Documents</b>.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section class="section case-page" id="tools-pdf-to-doc">
                    <h2>PDF to DOC Converter</h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>

                    <p>
                        The <b>PDF to DOC Converter</b> tool in <b>Mykase</b> allows you to seamlessly
                        convert PDF documents into editable Word (DOC) files.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        This feature is especially useful when you need to make quick edits, extract
                        information, or repurpose content from scanned or locked PDF files without
                        manually retyping the text.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        To convert any PDF file to a Doc file, please follow the steps below:
                    </p>
                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/tools7.png" alt="tools Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <ul>
                        <li>Go to the <b>Tools</b> section and select <b>PDF to DOC Converter</b>.</li>
                        <li>
                            Upload the PDF file you wish to convert by clicking on the
                            <b>Click to Upload</b> button.
                        </li>
                        <li>Click on the <b>Convert to Doc</b> button.</li>
                        <li>
                            Once the conversion is complete, download the editable Word document
                            by clicking on the <b>Download</b> button.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </section>



                <section class="section case-page" id="profile" style="display:none;">
                    <h2>Profile</h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>
                    <p>
                        The <b>Profile section</b> in Mykase allows each user to manage and personalize their account settings. From this section, users can update their personal information, organization details, security settings, and communication preferences. Keeping this information accurate ensures smooth functioning, secure access, and a personalized experience across the platform.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        To access the Profile section, you can click on the Profile Placeholder Icon on the top-right corner and select the Profile option from the menu.
                    </p>


                    <p>
                        <h4>
                            Key Features:
                        </h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <b>
                                    Personal & Organization Details
                                </b><br />
                                View and update your personal information such as name, email, mobile number, and designation. You can also modify organization-related details and upload your <b>company logo</b> for consistent branding.
                            </li>
                            <div>
                                <img src="~/newassets/img/UserManual/admin2.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                            </div>
                            <li>
                                <b>
                                    Email Verification
                                </b><br />
                                Verify your registered email address using an <b>OTP (One-Time Password)</b> to ensure account authenticity and uninterrupted delivery of alerts and notifications.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <b>

                                    Two-Factor Authentication (2FA)

                                </b>
                                Strengthen your account security by enabling or disabling <b>Two-Factor Authentication</b>. When enabled, you’ll be required to verify your identity through an additional OTP at login, adding an extra layer of protection. Simply toggle the Two Factor Authentication option under the <b>General Information</b> section

                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <b>
                                    Change Password

                                </b>
                                Update your password anytime for security reasons. It is recommended to use a strong password of a minimum of eight characters combining at least one uppercase letter, one lowercase letter, one number and one special character.

                                To change the password, please open the <b>Change Password</b> section under the profile.
                            </li>
                        </ul>


                    </p>


                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserManual/admin.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                </section>







                <section class="section case-page" id="notifications" style="display:none;">
                    <h2>Notifications </h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>


                    <p>
                        To view all your notifications, click the <b>bell icon</b> located on the top of the screen . This will display notifications related to your documents, matters, tasks, and time entries.
                    </p>
                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserManual/admin3.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>


                    <p>
                        Once you click on any notification, it redirects you to the origin and the notification is automatically marked as read.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Any read notification is indicated by green bell icon and unread notifications are indicated as orange bell icon .
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        You can mark any notification as read by clicking on the Mark as Read button or mark it as unread by cliking on <b>Mark as Read </b> button .
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        To mark all the notifications as read at once, you can click on <b>Mark all as Read</b>
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        For deleting any individual notification, you can click on <b>Delete</b> button and to delete all notifications, you can click on <b>Clear All</b> button .
                    </p>

                </section>






