            <main class="panel">
                <section class="section case-page" id="t3-dashboard">
                    <h2>AI Tools - Training Manual</h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>

                    <p>The <b>AI Tools</b> section in Mykase is designed to assist legal professionals in enhancing efficiency, accuracy, and decision-making through intelligent automation. These tools help users save time, improve accuracy, and get quick insights into case developments without manually going through lengthy documents. </p>
                    <p>Currently, the AI Tools section includes two key features: </p>


                    <h4>Generate Summary</h4>


                    <p>
                        The <b>Generate Summary</b> feature helps you quickly understand the essence of
                        any court order or judgment without reading through multiple pages.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        It automatically extracts and summarizes key details such as case background,
                        issues, directions from the court, and the final outcome.
                    </p>

                    <p><b>Key Highlights:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Converts lengthy orders into short, structured summaries.</li>
                        <li>Highlights critical portions such as decisions, observations, and next hearing details.</li>
                        <li>Saves time during case review and internal reporting.</li>
                        <li>Summaries can be stored within the matter for future reference.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <p><b>Please follow the below steps to generate the order summary:</b></p>
                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/GS1.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <ul>
                        <li>Click on the <b>AI Tools</b> option from the left menu and select the <b>Generate Summary</b> tab.</li>
                        <li>
                            On the screen, you will see all your active matters added in your
                            <b>Mykase</b> account. You can also search for a matter using
                            <b>Matter Name</b> or <b>Court Case No.</b>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            For any of the cases where you want to generate the summary, click on the
                            <b>View Orders</b> button corresponding to the case.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            From the popup, select up to <b>5 orders</b> for which the summary needs
                            to be generated. You can preview the orders using the <b>View</b> icon<img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/tview.png">.
                        </li>
                        <div>
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/GS2.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                        </div>

                        <li>
                            Please note that you can only select up to 5 orders for the summary generation.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            Once the orders are selected, finally click on the Generate Summary button.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            The generated summary will open in a new tab.
                        </li>


                    </ul>
                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/GS3.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>
                    <p>
                        In the summary, you can view the references through numbers which represent the orders selected for the summary generation. You can click on these numbers to view the orders from where the reference is taken.
                    </p>

                    <p><b>To share this order summary on email, please follow the below steps: </b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Click on the <b>Email</b> icon <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/email.png"> on the top-right corner of the summary.</li>
                        <div>
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/GS4.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                        </div>

                        <li>Enter the email ID and message in the popup and click on the <b>Send</b> button.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <p>
                        The summary can also be printed directly through the <b>Print</b> option.
                        Previously generated summaries can be viewed under the
                        <b>View Generated Summaries</b> section.
                    </p>
                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/GS5.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>
                </section>

                <section class="section case-page" id="t3-matterlist">
                    <h2>Generate Chronology</h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>

                    <p>
                        The <b>Generate Chronology</b> tool organizes case-related events into a
                        structured, date-wise sequence.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        It automatically identifies important actions, hearing dates, and orders
                        to create a comprehensive timeline of the case.
                    </p>

                    <p><b>Key Highlights:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Automatically extracts key events and arranges them chronologically.</li>
                        <li>Helps track the procedural flow of a case at a glance.</li>
                        <li>Ideal for internal analysis, client updates, and preparing case briefs.</li>
                        <li>The chronology can be downloaded or saved.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <p><b>Please follow the below steps to generate the case chronology:</b></p>
                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/GC1.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Click on the <b>AI Tools</b> option from the left menu and select the <b>Generate Chronology</b> tab.</li>
                        <li>
                            On the screen, you will see all your active matters added in your
                            <b>Mykase</b> account. You can also search for a matter using
                            <b>Matter Name</b> or <b>Court Case No.</b>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            For the case where you want to generate the chronology, click on the
                            <b>View Orders</b> button corresponding to the case.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            From the popup, select up to <b>5 orders</b> for which the chronology
                            needs to be generated. You can preview the orders using the <b>View</b> icon<img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/tview.png">.
                        </li>
                        <div>
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/GC2.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                        </div>

                        <li>Please note that you can only select up to 5 orders for the chronology generation. </li>
                        <li>
                            Once the orders are selected, finally click on the Generate Chronology button.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            The generated chronology will open in a new tab.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/GC3.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>
                    <p>
                        In the chronology, you can view the references through numbers which represent the orders selected for the chronology generation. You can click on these numbers to view the orders from where the reference is taken.
                    </p>

                    <p><b>To share the order chronology via email:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Click on the <b>Email</b> icon <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/email.png"> on the top-right corner of the chronology.</li>
                        <div>
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/GC4.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                        </div>
                        <li>Enter the email ID and message in the popup and click on the <b>Send</b> button.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>
                        The chronology can also be printed directly through the Print option <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/print.png">.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        You can view the previously generated chronology under the
                        <b>View Generated Chronologies</b> section as well.
                    </p>

                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/GC5.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>
                </section>


