                    <p>
                        The <b>IPR Management</b> module in <b>Mykase</b> helps you seamlessly manage
                        and track all types of intellectual property assets — including
                        <b>Trademarks</b>, <b>Copyrights</b>, <b>Patents</b>,
                        <b>Designs</b>, and <b>Geographical Indications (GI)</b> —
                        within a single, centralized platform.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        This section is designed to simplify IP monitoring, renewal tracking,
                        and document management, ensuring that your intellectual property
                        portfolio is always up to date and fully protected.
                    </p>

                    <h4>Dashboard</h4>


                    <p>
                        The <b>IPR Dashboard</b> in <b>Mykase</b> serves as a centralized control panel
                        that gives you a complete overview of all your intellectual property assets —
                        including <b>Trademarks</b>, <b>Copyrights</b>, <b>Patents</b>,
                        <b>Designs</b>, and <b>Geographical Indications (GI)</b> —
                        in a single, organized view.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        It provides quick insights, performance summaries, and status updates
                        to help you manage your IP portfolio efficiently and proactively.
                    </p>
                    <p>To access the IPR dashboard, click on the IPR option in the left menu and choose <b>Dashboard</b>. </p>
                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/IPDash.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <p>
                        You can also view a calendar displaying all your <b>hearings</b> and
                        <b>IPR renewals</b>, which can be highlighted and synced seamlessly
                        with your Google Calendar by clicking on the
                        <b>Sync to Google Calendar</b> button  <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/SYNC_TO_GC.png" />.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        To access the IPR dashboard, click on the <b>IPR</b> option in the left menu
                        and select <b>Dashboard</b>.
                    </p>
                </section>


                <!-- Placeholder sections (you will add content later) -->
                <section class="section case-page" id="ipr-trademark-search">
                    <h2>Trademark</h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>

                    <p>
                        The <b>Trademark</b> section under the IPR Management module allows you to
                        efficiently track, manage, and monitor all your trademark applications
                        and registrations in one place.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        It helps ensure that your trademarks remain protected, compliant,
                        and up to date throughout their lifecycle.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        You can access the Trademark section by clicking on the
                        <b>IPR</b> option and choosing <b>Trademark</b> from the left menu.
                    </p>
                    <h4>Search and Add Trademark</h4>


                    <p>
                        The <b>Trademark Addition</b> feature in <b>Mykase</b> allows you to add
                        and manage details of your trademark applications and registrations
                        in a structured manner.
                    </p>

                    <p><b>There are three ways to add a Trademark:</b></p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Through Trademark Search</li>
                        <li>Through Proprietor Search</li>
                        <li>Through Agent Search</li>
                    </ol>

                    <p><b>Add through Trademark Search:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Navigate to <b>IPR Management → Trademark</b>.</li>
                        <li>Click on <b>Add Trademark</b> button  <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/addtrademark.png" /> on the top right of the screen.</li>
                        <li>Click on the <b>Trademark</b> tab.</li>
                        <div>
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/SAT1.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                        </div>
                        <li>
                            Enter the trademark name or application number to search
                            for the trademark in the registry.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            You can narrow your search using filters such as
                            Jurisdiction, Class, Status, Date of Application or Proprietor Name.
                        </li>
                        <li>Click on the <b>Search</b> button to view results.</li>
                        <li>
                            From the list, you can add any trademark to your tracker by
                            clicking on the <b>Add</b> <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Add1.png" /> button under the action column.
                        </li>


                        <li>

                            You can also view additional trademark information by clicking on the
                            <b>Trademark Information</b> button under the action column.

                        </li>
                        <div>
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/SAT2.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                        </div>

