                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Dtracker2.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <p>
                        The same information can also be emailed directly as an excel by clicking on
                        the <b>Email as Excel</b> button
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/emailasexcel.png" />.
                    </p>

                    <h4>Applicant Search</h4>
                    <div class="hr"></div>

                    <p>
                        Please find below the steps to search through <b>Applicant Search</b>:
                    </p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>Navigate to <b>IPR Management → Design</b>.</li>
                        <li>
                            Click on <b>Add Design</b> button
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/ADD_DESIGN.png" />
                            on the top right of the screen.
                        </li>
                        <li>Click on the <b>Applicant</b> tab.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Dtracker3.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Now, enter the <b>Applicant Address</b> to search for the Design in the registry.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Click on the <b>Search</b> button to view the results.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Below the search bar, you will see all the information of the
                            <b>Applicant Address</b>.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            The information of any <b>particular applicant</b> can be downloaded by
                            clicking on the <b>Download</b> button
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/down.png" />
                            under the action column.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            From the list, you can view the Design information for any
                            <b>particular applicant</b> by clicking on the
                            <b>View Applicant Details</b> button
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/VIEW.png" />
                            under the action column.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            In the popup, you will see the information of the Design filed by the Applicant.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Dtracker4.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>
                    <p>
                        The information can be emailed directly as an excel by clicking on the
                        <b>Email as Excel</b> button
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/emailasexcel.png" />.
                    </p>

                    <h4>Design- Tracker</h4>
                    <div class="hr"></div>

                    <p>
                        All the <b>Design</b> added to your tracker can be accessed by navigating to
                        the <b>IPR</b> option in the left menu and choosing <b>Design</b>.
                    </p>

                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Dtracker5.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <p>
                        In the tracker, you can view the information of the Design such as
                        <b>Design Name, Applicant, Status, Date of Filing, Class,</b>
                        <b>Journal No.</b> and <b>Application No.</b>.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        You can search for any Design using the <b>Search</b> feature
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/SEARCH.png" />
                        which gives you the option to narrow your search based on
                        <b>Application No., Journal No., Status, Date of Filing,</b>
                        <b>Class</b>, etc.
                    </p>

                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Dtracker6.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <p>
                        The information can be downloaded locally into your system by clicking on
                        the <b>Download</b> button
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/down.png" />.
                    </p>

                    <h4>Action Buttons on Tracker</h4>
                    <div class="hr"></div>

                    <p>
                        In the tracker, there are action buttons given under the
                        <b>Action</b> tab, which can be used to do various activities.
                        Please find the details of the buttons as below:
                    </p>

                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Dtracker6.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <b>View Design Details</b>
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/tview.png" />
                            – The option is used to view the information of the Design such as
                            Design Number, Class, Applicant Details, Date of Registration, etc.
                            From the popup, you can use the <b>Email as Excel</b> button
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/EMAIL_EXCEL.png" />
                            which allows you to share the Design details instantly with team members
                            or clients through email.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <b>Delete Design</b>
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/tdel.png" />
                            – The user can mark the Design for deletion to permanently remove the
                            selected Design record from the tracker if it is no longer relevant.
                            The final action on the deletion or restoration is taken by the admin.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                </section>



                <section class="section case-page" id="ipr-design-mylist">
                    <h2>Design-My List</h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>

                    <p>
                        The <b>My List</b> section in the <b>Design Management</b> module serves as a
                        dedicated space to store and manage all <b>manually added Designs</b> that are
                        not automatically tracked through the official registry.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        When a Design is added manually for internal reference or record-keeping,
                        it gets saved under <b>My List</b>. This allows users to maintain complete
                        visibility over both tracked and untracked IP assets within the system.
                    </p>

                    <p><b>To access My List, please follow the below steps:</b></p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>Click on <b>IPR</b> option in the left menu.</li>
                        <li>Choose <b>Design</b> option.</li>
                        <li>Click on the <b>My List</b> tab.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Dml.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <p>
                        In the list, you can view all your manually added Designs.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        To export the details of the Design, click on the <b>Export</b> button and
                        choose the method you want i.e. <b>Export to Excel</b> or <b>Export to PDF</b>.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        The added Design can be edited using the <b>Edit</b> button
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/VIEW_PEN.png" />
                        under the action tab and the <b>Delete</b> button can be used to delete
                        the Design from My List.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class="section case-page" id="ipr-design-history">
                    <h2>Design-Search History</h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>

                    <p>
                        The <b>Search History</b> tab keeps a record of all your previous searches
                        conducted within the <b>Design Module</b>. Each search entry is automatically
                        saved for future references.
                    </p>

                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Dsh.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>
                    <p>
                        For any individual Design, you can click on the <b>Search</b> button
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/MAGNIFY.png" />
                        to conduct the search again for the same Design.
                    </p>
                </section>


                <section class="section case-page" id="ipr-design-delete">

                    <h2>Design-Delete Request</h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>

                    <p>
                        The <b>Delete Request List</b> serves as a control panel for the <b>admin</b>
                        to review and take final action on Designs that have been
                        <b>marked for deletion</b> by users.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        This feature ensures that no Design record is permanently removed without
                        administrative review, maintaining data <b>security</b> and preventing
                        accidental deletions of important records.
                    </p>

                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Ddh.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <p>
                        You can use the <b>Filter</b> feature
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/FILTERS.png" />
                        which gives you the option to narrow your search based on
                        <b>Design Name</b> or <b>Design Number</b>.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        The admin can take the final action on deletion of Design by either
                        deleting it permanently or restoring it back to the tracker by
                        clicking on the <b>Delete</b> button
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/tdel.png" />
                        or <b>Restore</b> button
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/restore.png" />
                        respectively.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class="section case-page" id="ipr-resources">

                    <h2>Resources</h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>

                    <p>
                        The <b>Resources</b> section serves as a <b>reference library</b> within the
                        IPR Management module, providing quick access to essential information and
                        documents related to intellectual property classification and filing.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        It is designed to help users make accurate and informed decisions while filing
                        or managing their trademarks and designs.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        To access the <b>Resources</b> section, click on the <b>IPR</b> option and choose
                        <b>Resources</b>.
                    </p>

                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/RESORCES.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <b>Trademark Class Details:</b><br>
                            This document provides a complete list of <b>Nice Classification (NCL)</b>
                            trademark classes (<b>Class 1–45</b>), along with detailed descriptions of
                            goods and services covered under each class.
                            <br><br>
                            It helps users accurately identify the appropriate class for filing new
                            trademarks, ensuring applications are filed under the correct category
                            and minimizing the risk of objections or rejections.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <b>Design Details:</b><br>
                            This section includes a comprehensive <b>Design Classification</b> document
                            outlining the <b>Locarno Classification</b> used for registering industrial
                            designs.
                            <br><br>
                            It enables users to refer to the correct category of products or articles
                            when filing or tracking Design applications.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

            </main>

