                <section class="section case-page" id="ipr-dashboard">
                    <h2>Dashboard </h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>


                    <p>The <b>Notice Management Dashboard</b> serves as the central hub for managing all your notices — whether sent or received. It provides a complete overview of the notice lifecycle, helping users monitor the progress, deadlines, and related actions efficiently. </p>


                    <p>
                        To access the Notice Dashboard, you can click on the <b>Notice</b> option on the left menu and choose Dashboard from the list.
                    </p>
                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/Ndash.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>



                    <p><b>Key Highlights:</b></p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <b> Comprehensive Overview: </b> The dashboard displays all notices — sent and received .
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <b> Status Tracking: </b> Each notice is shown with its current status — such as Civil, Consumer, etc.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <b> Calendar Integration: </b> The dashboard integrates with your calendar view, displaying all notice-related due, which can also be synced with your Google calendar by clicking on the Sync button
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/sync.png" /> .
                        </li>
                    </ul>



                </section>



                <section class="section case-page" id="send-all-notice-list">

                    <h2>Send Notices-All Notice List</h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>


                    <p>
                        The <b>Send Notices</b> page provides a complete list of all notices that
                        have been <b>created and sent to counterparties</b>. It acts as a central
                        workspace where users can easily track, manage, and take action on every
                        notice that has been dispatched from the system.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        To access the <b>Send Notices</b> section, click on the <b>Notice</b> option
                        on the left menu and choose <b>Notice List</b>.
                    </p>

                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/SendNotices1.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <h4>Key Highlights</h4>


                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <b>Comprehensive List of Sent Notices:</b><br>
                            View all notices that have been sent to clients, vendors, or other
                            counterparties. Each entry displays essential details such as
                            <b>notice type, subject, priority, mode of delivery, assigned user,</b>
                            and <b>current status</b>.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <b>Status Tracking:</b><br>
                            Instantly view the current progress of each notice — whether it is
                            <b>Active, Inactive, Settled,</b> or <b>Converted to Matter</b>.
                            This helps ensure that every notice is properly followed up.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <b>Quick Filters:</b><br>
                            Use built-in filters to narrow down your search based on
                            <b>notice type, sender name, subject, priority, date range,</b>
                            or <b>status</b>, allowing you to locate any notice in seconds.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <b>Bulk Share:</b><br>
                            Select multiple notices using the checkboxes beside each record
                            to share multiple notices with team members by clicking on the
                            <b>Share Multiple</b> button <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/SHARE.png" /> in the Send Notices List.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <b>Custom View:</b><br>
                            Customize the displayed columns by selecting your preferred fields
                            using the <b>Customize</b> option, <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/customize.png" /> ensuring the layout aligns with
                            your workflow preferences.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <b>Export and Reporting:</b><br>
                            Export the complete or filtered list of sent notices in
                            <b>Excel</b> format for recordkeeping, reporting, or internal analysis.
                            To export the list, click on the <b>Export</b> button <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/export.png" /> and choose the
                            method i.e. <b>Export to Excel</b> or <b>Export to PDF</b>.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                </section>




                <section class="section case-page" id="send-create-notice">

                    <h2>Send Notices-Create Notice</h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>

                    <p>
                        The <b>Create Notice</b> feature allows you to draft and issue new legal notices directly from the MyKase platform. It helps you capture all essential details, define priorities, and set up alerts — ensuring every notice is created, tracked, and sent efficiently.
                    </p>

                    <h4>Please follow the below steps to create a notice on Mykase: </h4>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Click on the <b>Notice</b> option in the left menu and choose
                            <b>Notice List</b>.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            Under <b>Send Notices</b>, click on the
                            <b>Create New Notice</b> button
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/CREATE_NEW_FOLDER.png" />.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            Enter the <b>Internal Number</b>, <b>Reference Number</b>, and
                            <b>Sender</b> details.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            Add the <b>Receiver</b> details to specify who the notice is intended for.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            Select the <b>Notice Type</b> (Statutory or Non-Statutory) from the dropdown.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            Fill in the notice information such as <b>Title</b>, <b>Subject</b>,
                            <b>Date of Notice</b>, <b>Due Date</b>, and <b>Mode of Delivery</b>.
                        </li>
                        <li>Please note that whatever details are being filed in the form, will also be accommodated in the notice builder. </li>
                        <div>
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/SendNoticescreate1.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                        </div>
                        <li>
                            You can draft the rest of the notice body in the Notice Builder.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            Once all required details are added, click on the <b>Save</b> button
                            to create the notice.
                        </li>
                    </ul>



                    <h4>Action buttons on Send Notices list</h4>


                    <p>
                        Each notice listed under the <b>Send Notices</b> page comes with several action buttons that
                        allow users to manage, update, and track notices efficiently. Below are the details of each
                        button and its functionality:
                    </p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <b>View More</b>  <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/VIEW.png" />- Displays the Notice Text which is created in the Notice Builder.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <b>View Notice Draft</b> <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/FOLDER.png" /> - Opens the list of all drafted versions of the notice that was created and sent.
                            This allows users to review the original content and verify the details of the drafted communication.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/SendNoticescreate2.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <p>
                        The draft versions can also be sent through email directly from the system by entering the email ID
                        in the popup and clicking on <b>Send</b> button.
                    </p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <b>Edit Notice</b> <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/VIEW_PEN.png" /> - Enables users to modify or update an existing notice. This option is useful if any
                            corrections, additional information, or changes are needed before further action is taken.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <b>Share Notice</b><img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/SHARE.png" /> - Allows users to share the notice directly with internal team members or external parties
                            within the system. This helps in collaboration and review without downloading or manually forwarding the document.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/SendNoticescreate7.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <b>Set Alert</b> <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/setalert.png" /> - Lets users set automated reminders for follow-ups, responses, or deadlines related to a
                            particular notice. Alerts can be configured for specific dates and times to ensure no milestone is missed.
                        </li>
                    </ul>


                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/SendNoticescreate3.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <b>Add Details</b> <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/ADD.png" /> - Used to record any subsequent replies connected to the notice. This helps in maintaining
                            a comprehensive record of all communications and actions taken.


                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/SendNoticescreate4.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>
                    <p>
                        All the added rejoinders/replies will be available under the Original Notice and can be viewed by clicking on
                        the <b>View More Item</b> button.
                    </p>


                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/SendNoticescreate5.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <b>View Feedback</b> <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/VIEW_FEED.png" /> - Displays feedback or comments received from the counterparty or internal stakeholders
                            regarding the notice. This promotes transparency and helps track responses efficiently.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <b>Upload Document</b> <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/uploaddocu.png" /> - Allows users to upload supporting documents or any correspondence associated with the notice.
                            These uploaded files are stored in a centralized repository for quick reference.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <b>Save Dispatch Details</b> <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/SAVE.png" /> - Used to record dispatch-related details such as the mode of delivery, consignment number,
                            and date of dispatch. The system automatically tracks the notice status, provided it has been sent through Indian Post.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/SendNoticescreate6.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <b>Mark Status</b> <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/MARK_STATUS.png" /> - Enables users to update the current stage of the notice — for example, <b>Active</b>, <b>Inactive</b>,
                            <b>Settled</b> or <b>Converted to Matter</b>. Keeping the status updated helps in clear progress tracking and reporting.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <b>Archive</b> <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/ARCHIVE.png" /> - Moves the notice from the active list to the <b>Archived Notices</b> section once it has been completed or
                            closed. Archiving helps declutter the active list while retaining records for future reference.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <b>Delete</b> <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/tdel.png" /> - Allows authorized users to mark a notice for deletion. Deleted notices can be permanently removed after admin
                            approval from the <b>Delete Request List</b>, ensuring no accidental data loss.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <b>Connect to Matter</b> <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/CONNECT_TO_MATTER.png" /> - Once the status of the notice is changed to <b>Converted to Matter</b>, this option becomes available
                            to link the notice to a related matter in the MyKase system. This integration ensures all communications, documents, and actions
                            related to a specific case are accessible from one centralized location.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </section>



