                <section class="section notice-bulk-notices" id="bulk-temp">

                    <h2>Bulk Notices</h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>

                    <p>
                        The <b>Bulk Notices</b> section allows you to create and send multiple notices at once,
                        saving significant time and effort compared to creating each notice individually.
                        This feature is especially useful when sending identical or similar notices to
                        several recipients such as <b>clients, vendors, or counterparties</b>.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        You can access the <b>Bulk Notices</b> section by clicking on the <b>Notice</b> option
                        in the left menu and choosing <b>Bulk Notices</b>.
                    </p>

                    <p>The process of creating bulk notices involves <b>two main steps:</b> </p>


                    <h4>Template Creation</h4>

                    <p>
                        In this step, you create a <b>standardized template</b> containing the content and
                        structure of the notice. You can define the <b>type, subject, and body</b> of the notice
                        and save it for repeated use.Templates can also be edited or modified later if any updates are required.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        To create a template, please follow the below steps:
                    </p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Click on the <b>Notice</b> option in the left menu and choose <b>Bulk Notices</b>.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Click on the <b>Templates</b> tab.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/tempcre1.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Click on the <b>Create Template</b> button
                            <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/CREATE_TEMPLATE.png" />.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            On the new screen, enter the <b>Template Name</b> under the <b>Create Template</b> box, draft the body of the notice.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <div>
                        <img src="~/newassets/img/UserMatterManual/tempcre2.png" alt="admin Overview" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" style="max-width: 600px;">
                    </div>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            While creating the template, you need to add variables in the below format:
                            <ul>
                                <li><b>#Name#</b></li>
                                <li><b>#Address#</b></li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            Apart from the variables, the rest of the notice body can remain the <b>same</b>.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Once the template is created, click on the <b>Save Template</b> button to store the template
                            for future bulk notice creation.
                        </li>


                    </ul>



                </section>




                <section class="section case-page" id="bulk-rec">

                    <h2>Bulk Notices-Recipient List Creation</h2>
                    <div class="hr"></div>

                    <p>
                        After finalizing the template, you need to create the <b>Recipient List</b>.
                        This list contains the values for the variables defined in your template.
                        For example, if your template includes variables such as
                        <b>#Name#, #Address#, or #Date#</b>, then the headers in your Excel sheet
                        should use the same terms (<b>Name, Address, Date</b>) without the hashtags.
                        This ensures that the system correctly maps each recipient’s information
                        while generating and sending the bulk notices.
                    </p>

                    <h4>Sending the Notice</h4>


                    <p>
                        Once the recipient list is created, you can generate bulk notices by
                        following the steps below:
                    </p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Click on the <b>Notice</b> option in the left menu and choose
                            <b>Bulk Notices</b>.
